column17: Event
column30: event

column17: The last two days have been notably uneventful. The only thing that comes to mind on this count is that earlier today, I was helping someone attempt to track down a specific tool to open the screws on the bottom of their computer. I'm generally good with this kind of stuff, and found it in no time at all. Despite this, and after showing them the information, they proceeded to continue looking online for the tool they needed, and ultimately ordered the wrong one. I finally just gave up. Nothing huge, but irritating nonetheless.
column30: This situation is definitely not as negative as it seemed at the time, or sort of feels at the moment. While I can't say there are any silver linings, I can definitely say that the overarching lesson is to simply mind my own business when it's clear I need to, and let people just make their mistakes as they see fit without feeling compelled to correct them. The situation is not permanent by any means, and the only real improvement needed is within my own outlook. the rest is honestly none of my business.

column17: A situation that took place in the past two days is when my car ran out of gas right before I got to the gas station. I procrastinated on putting gas in my car and then I ran out of gas in the middle of the road. I had to walk to the store and get a can with gas and walk back. I felt irritated about this. My current thoughts and feelings toward the event is that it is funny now thinking about it.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems. It is not a big deal to run out of gas for your car, you just have to make sure it does not happen again. The silver lining to this situation is that it taught me a valuable lesson about procrastinating, especially when it comes to your main mode of transportation. No there is nothing I could learn useful from this situation except to not procrastinate on things that are important. The situation is not permanent and it can be improved in the future by me taking care of things before they turn into a bad situation.

column17: I saw a picture of a dude on an MTurk survey and the top of his mouth was either covered in extra teeth or fungus. I couldn't tell which, and usually disgusting pictures don't bother me, but that one did.
column30: It was just a stupid survey. It's bothering me now, but that feeling will go away eventually. It was just something disgusting that stuck in my mind.

column17: My son started a new school today. I feel bad as I could not afford his private school tuition anymore.
column30: I’m hoping he gets excited about the new school and meeting new friends. I hope he lives his teachers and having a bigger class

column17: I work in a nursing home,and we had a resident pass yesterday morning. This made me very sad,as this was one of my very favorite residents. She never has visitors,and would always meet me at the menu board every morning when I would get to work. Yesterday morning,she didnt meet me. I was going to o to her room and see how she was,but decided to wait until after breakfast. She passed during that time. I will never know now if I had gone to see her,if it would have made a difference to her.
column30: It is a negative situation,however it had its bright side. She passed away,but now she is no longer suffering,she is no longer lonely,she is no longer crying because her family didnt come around. She loved me,and I her. She knew I cared for her. I will always remember her,and think of how we made each other laugh every morning at that menu board! And that will make me smile.

column17: In the past two days an event that happened that still bothers me is when I went out to the bowling alley with some friends. During this time we were all having drinks, bowling, laughing and having a good time. During this time one of the other people at the bowling alley came over and started to make rude comments to us. Because of this I got mad and started arguing with the person. We all ended up getting kicked out of the bowling alley. During this time it made me feel bad because I felt that I acted in a immature way, got us kicked out, and let everyone in my group down.
column30: When I think about this situation I do not think it is as negative as it seems because I was sticking up for my group of friends and they told me they were happy that I did not let them talk to us that way. Some silver linings that I can think of to the situation is that I proved to my friends how loyal and trustworthy I am. I am able to stand up for them and do anything for them. What I could learn from this situation is that I am a very loyal person that protects my family and friends. I can also learn that I could work on my attitude and learn to make it into a positive. This situation is not permanent, because it was a small one time event that did not really have a long term effect on any of us. All that happen was that we left and went back to one of our houses and still had a good time.

column17: Someone was supposed to contact me today so that I could have helped them with something. They never did, but I kind of wished that they had. It would have been better if I had helped them today because of how my schedule is arranged, so if I have to help them later, it might be sub optimal for me in certain ways. Or, perhaps, they tried to proceed without my help, which might make me feel bad because I should have been more proactive in reaching out to them. Either way, I feel like this situation is not fully resolved when I expected it to be, so that is making me stressed, if nothing else.
column30: Perhaps I am worrying too much about this situation. I have been in this kind of predicament before, and oftentimes, it just happens that the person was too busy to contact me, and they'll do so at a later date. Everyone will be fine with what happens as long as I help this person when they ask me to, even if it is not at the absolute best time for me. Either way, I don't really feel like this is a permanent problem - it will somehow be resolved in due time because it does not concern a major issue.

column17: A guy that i have been dating has been ignoring my texts. I was really excited about him so it was really hard to be ignored. I am really sad and can;t stop my mind from racing about it.
column30: It is not really as negative as it seems. The silver lining is that he probably wasn't right for me. I can learn to be better about dating and not get all in.

column17: Yesterday I learned that my sister has been avoiding me for the past several weeks because of something that I said. I immediately felt bad because saying something that would hurt my sister was not intentional on my part. I feel kind of sad and regretful that I let something like this happen.
column30: My sister was willing to explain what upset her so that she's not so upset that she's unwilling to talk to me. In my long relationship with my sister, we've had a lot of ups and downs that we've always managed to overcome. I learned an important lesson in sensitivity in thanks to the situation. My sister and I will move on from this situation, it just may some time. I think that talking about our feelings together more honestly should help to improve the situation.

column17:
So, last time I wrote about a dog whose owners were visiting my parents.  My parents and i share a house with my children and husband. The dog was aggressive to me when I tried letting it out to use the bathroom. 
Well, my 4 year old has been saying the dog bit him.  I told him the dog just scratched him and we went on with our lives.  He was still scared of the dog, but I joked and said he is just a cat person (we currently have no pets). Come to find out as the guests were leaving, the dog did nip at him and my nephews, who were visiting one of the days this weekend.  I felt terribly guilty for joking around and telling him the dog didn't attack him.  I pulled my 4 year old aside and apologized for not believing him. I still feel bad, like i should have listened to him instead of not believing him.
column30:
The situation isn't really that negative.  Kiddo is over it already, but I still feel really guilty. 

A silver lining could be that this will teach me to be a little more attentive to what he's telling me.  He repeatedly said to me and my husband that the dog bit him, but because he's young, we figured the dog just scratched him because it was excited. He also completely avoided the dog, which is great because if a dog is not so nice, we don't want him approaching it. 

The situation isn't permanent.  The guests left this morning so they will never see the dog again.

column17: There was not much to do over the weekend. I didn't have anybody to do anything with because a neighbor has been slandering my name for  9 years now and a lot of people believe her lies and they tell people the lie and it's a small town and every time I become friends with somebody, they try to find out and turn the person against me , for revenge. I am very upset and have to move out of state because of them,
column30: Yea, I am going to move somewhere else.  I am so happy to get away from those creepy evil people and I love where I am at now. And there will be normal positive people there that I can talk to and not have to worry that they are trying to set me up or pretending they are my friend so they can tell vile people what I said so they can use it against me. Those vile people were caught and are in jail now.

column17: I posted a comic on reddit, that I had worked hard on. It was just a 4 panel webcomic, but I spent a lot of time on it and have been trying to improve my skills. Some of the commenters made fun of the artwork and said it was terrible. It makes me feel bad that even though I tried hard at something, the results weren't good enough. It makes me feel like I don't have talent or potential for drawing. It also gets me down that other people would be mean to a stranger for no reason.
column30: I will try to see the truth in the negative comments, and use the advice to fuel my motivation. There is a good chance that the people were just leaving comments to be mean, and weren't giving me an objective review of my work. I know that in the future there will be negative people, it happens to everyone, and I just need to expect it and ignore it. There is always room for improvement in art, and if I keep working at it I will certainly improve.

column17: On Sunday I was supposed to hang out with my friend Jeff. It has been a while since we saw each other. We were gonna playing video games. I had a very busy weekend on Friday and Saturday and was exhausted. I bailed on him at the last minute and made up an excuse saying that I was sick. I feel bad because I should of just been honest with him. It was the wrong thing today and I regret it. I should of either hung out for a few hours or explained why I didn't want to hang that day.
column30: This is definitely not as negative as it seems. In the scheme of things, it is not a big deal. We could just hang out next weekend. I say that I should just be more honest and open in situations like these. This helps out in the long run with relationships. The situation can be improved by making an effort to see Jeff this week/weekend.

column17: My brother was around the house last night. I've been staying with my parents and he was upstairs trying to convince them to let him use their car and to give him money. He was claiming to need it to go to dialysis in another town that's pretty far away. He doesn't need dialysis he comes up with a new terrible story every week or two to get money or favors from them. I tell them to ignore him and stop giving him things, but they won't. So there's not much I can do except feel stressed about it.
column30: The situation isn't the end of the world. I don't need anything from my parents except for a place to stay so it doesn't hurt me directly. I know better than to do or give anything to him after observing how he treats my parents so at least I'm not getting taken. The situation will likely improve when he inevitably end up back in jail.

column17: I keep thinking about the different things I could have right now in terms of diseases, past 2 days it's been my UTI like symptoms. I am still stressing over it to a great extent because I'm not really sure since I haven't been diagnosed.
column30: For the most part, UTI symptoms are generally not dangerous unless it goes untreated, I will be seeing the doctor soon. I think that taking a step back its not as bad as it seems but its still worrisome. The other good thing is that the situation is not a permanent thing, I believe that going to the doctor will make me feel much better and ill stop being so anxious about the issue.

column17: I had to complete a hard project for work and I wasn't able to do it in time. This made me feel bad and I was worried about how others would view me.
column30: I think that I did the best I could on the assignment for work so I have no real reason to feel bad. And I think in the future I would do better.

column17: My father wanted me to help him work on something he needed for his work, except he doesn't have a computer so he needed to use mine. Because I was preoccupied with helping him, I was unable to successfully look for and complete HITs during that time period, which makes me annoyed because it's essentially my job. The situation is also annoying because the work he needed done shouldn't really be his responsibility anyway and someone else should be doing to begin with. Currently I don't feel as annoyed as when it first happened, but I am still slightly bothered by the whole situation.
column30: I can reframe the situation by thinking that this gave me an opportunity to learn more about my father's work and possibly offer him some advice on what to do in the future, it also provided me with a bonding experience in the sense that we can both talk about how annoyed we are by the situation, and sort of laugh about it later on. Certainly I don't think the situation is as negative as I felt when it was happening, and the situation probably isn't permanent and could definitely improve.

column17: The weekly email concerning taking extra hours that are available came this morning (for my regular job), as usual for Mondays. Typically, I never have a problem in securing the additional time that I want to work every week, so as I was distracted with other tasks, I did not respond right away. By the time I did make my request there were no more available. I am worried that perhaps this may become a competitive situation and I will have trouble securing the extra money/hours that I am accustomed. I was berating myself a bit for procrastinating. I am agitated.
column30: This has happened in the past, and it has not turned into a recurring event. It's very possible with kids returning to school people assume they have all this extra time now, and that belief always diminishes fast. I don't necessarily NEED the extra money, and the amount realistically is not significant nor will it impact my finances negatively. I would get along okay with my normal salary, and the extra hours are just a perk. I will have more time for other activities. If I remained focused on the financial loss, I can always spend more time on Mturk. I am usually pretty burned out and miserable with work by the end of the week, so I truly do need a break.

column17: Yesterday afternoon I got a notification that someone had posted a comment on one of my videos that I have on youtube. The comment was a negative one, saying that I shouldn't talk so much in my videos because my voice is really annoying. Deep down I know I have a really annoying voice and my commentary isn't the best though it still both annoys and hurts me to have to hear it. I didn't response to his comment and I didn't delete it because I don't believe in censorship. I'm still a little bit peeved about it but I know it's nothing big in the grand scheme of things.
column30: Truthfully the situation isn't really that bad. IT's just what some person on the internet thinks. The people who enjoy watching my videos still enjoy watching them and I they still want me to make more of them. I could learn not to take other peoples opinions too seriously and not to care so much about what strangers think of me. The situation isn't really permanent. Their opinion probably won't change, but they're such a small part of my life that they're little more than a passing memory.

column17: I've had a head cold for the past several days, which has been slowing me down work wise. I am upset that I missed getting an mturk qual that I would have liked to get, but you have to do a certain amount of tasks to get the qual and I just wasn't feeling up to it, and now regret that decision. I feel a lot of regret for not pushing through, since I could have made a decent amount of money doing those hits.
column30: Right now, the situation seems pretty bad, but you never know with mturk. I don't want to dwell in the situation, just push forward. There might actually be a silver lining. I'll just have to wait and see. I can learn a valuable lesson from this. That's the way mturk operates, you have to do the work when it it available and not wait for a better time. Now's the time. The situation could improve if they post more qual hits when I'm feeling better and therefore my thinking will be better and I might do better on them at this later time.

column17: I went to Target to buy new running  shoes. There was children playing in the Allies and they were out of my  size ... total waste of time. I have to go somewhere else , probably  big five.
column30: I will  solve the problem  tomorrow I will go to big 5 sports and get a better choice. Have I learned  something? Yes don't  go to Target and waste your time.

column17: Yesterday I wrote a long email to someone denigrating another person.  I felt quite accurate and justified in my appraisal.  Today, the person I denigrated proved themself to be doing at all what I portrayed them to be doing.  I feel low and ashamed.  I did email to the person I denigrated the person to and say I was completely wrong in this instance.  I still feel low. I maligned someone behind their back, and I do still think I'm accurate in my appraisal but I didn't have to spread dirt and in this case which is really the relevant one, I was wrong.
column30: I rarely ever denigrate anyone.  Like really.  So the obvious situation here would be to turn it around and say that I learned not to do it in the future but I do it so rarely that that's not even a really feasible thing as far as finding a silver lining.  Besides the denigration there were many other things I discussed with the other person that I don't usually discuss (it was like a springboard) so maybe I can say that it brought me closer to another person in an offshoot kind of way.  But doing so at the expense of another person isn't really a silver lining.  I just feel small.

column17: My uncle and I got into an argument, even though it should have never happened.  He was pissed about something and he said something that I wasn't too fond of, so I chimed in a quick rebuttal back at him.   He's pretty old school and figured that I disrespected him so he went on a long rant.  I took the high ground and remained calm while he ranted on.  I'm sure hes still pretty upset about it like I am.  I don't need that stuff in my life right now.
column30: Everyone fights sometimes, even family.  As long as we're able to get past it and move on without keeping our feelings hurt, we will come out of it stronger.

column17: I had to pay some bills but there was a severe lack of work available for me to do. This still bothers me because I am in the middle of fixing the situation but it has only improved slightly.
column30: While the situation is causing me stress, I am making some progress and will eventually be able to sort things out this week. The situation is not permanent and as time goes on I will be able to deal with it better.

column17: My dog has been urinating on my furniture. I had suspected that she was not potty trained when I got her (she is 2.5 years old), but just kept trying to train her. She had been doing well for a long time (over a month) but in the last week she has urinated on my bed, and now also on the couch. It was the second time that she had urinated on the bed, so it was very upsetting. Now we have to keep her in her crate at night as well as when I am at work. Now that she urinated on the couch, I am concerned she might have a urinary tract infection, so I made an appointment to take her in to the vet later this week.
column30: I am trying my best to be as positive as I can because I have read that how you react to it will really affect the dog if it is a behavior issue, so I did yell "NO" when I caught her urinating on the couch, but I have been trying to focus on positive reinforcement when she does go outside like she is suppose to and give her treats. I am hopeful that it has a medical reason so it can be resolved, but I am committed to helping her get potty trained if it isn't because I love her and I like to think that I would not give up on her. I do think it will make me a better pet owner to learn more about behavior problems so that in the future I will get better at recognizing problems and training them more efficiently. I do think this problem is temporary, and as infuriating as it might be we will get through it.

column17: I declined going out to lunch with my coworkers. Instead I worked through my lunch. I feel I could have had a better day if I took time out to socialize.
column30: I declined going out to lunch with some coworkers. I used that time to finish working on an important project.

column17: My car is broken 2 days ago. My car is out of battery and I had to call a friend to help me to jump start my car. I waited for an hour because my friend lives quite far from my location. I was so stressed out in the car. And feel regret for not changing my dead battery until it is too late. Now everything is fine. The battery is changed. I feel relief.
column30: It is not that negative though consider I did get a help from a friend of mine. I learned that I need to change the car battery every once in a while to avoid this kind of situation again. This situation is temporary and can be improved over time.

column17: I was committed to a mental facility and I felt very bad about myself.  Now I feel happy that I got the help I needed.
column30: I was committed to a mental health facility and got the help I needed.  I believe this was very good for me as it got me on the right medication.

column17: Have not had anything terribly notable happen that fits this bill. Closest example I can think of is something that happened on Twitter today. In response to a tweet about John Brennan being central to the capture of Osama bin Laden, I RT'd it with commentary essentially noting that Brennan was solely responsible for terrorizing Yemen with drone strikes throughout his tenure at CIA, as well as the deaths of 4 US citizens, including a 16 year old, and does not deserve the whitewashing he is currently receiving form the left. Though accurate, it definitely made me feel bad as I was mostly just angry, and being a jerk, and still feel a bit like one.
column30: I mean, given that it's just something on social media, the situation, in perspective is not overwhelmingly negative nor terribly far reaching. While there are no silver linings that I see, I think the lesson to be learned is that sometimes it's better to simply say nothing at all when I'm upset. The situation is not permanent; I can go delete the information whenever I want, and probably should, as it was not something written with an agenda of helpfulness.

column17: I basically took it easy at work and didn't do much of anything yesterday.  I watched TV and read, but didn't accomplish much.  I wasn't focused and just felt as if I needed a break.
column30: It was nice to not work very hard yesterday as I needed to recharge my batteries so to speak.  This made me more energetic and devoted today so it worked out well.

column17: Something that happened recently that bothered me is that I did not get enough sleep because  there is not enough time in the day. I was tired yesterday because I had stayed up almost all night playing a video game. I had to buy a energy drink to stay awake. My thoughts and feelings toward the incident is that it was negative but worth it. It was worth it to learn that I need my sleep. I had to learn that I cannot function on 4 hours of sleep.
column30: This situation is not a big deal. I learned not to underestimate the standard 8 hours of sleep I need a night. This situation is not permanent. I can improve it by simply getting enough sleep like I usually do.

column17: I tried to complete the survey for this ongoing HIT yesterday, but then I forgot about it and tried to do it later in the day and it said all the HITs were unavailable. This made me frustrated at myself for procrastinating and losing the opportunity, and it also made me confused at why there wasn't enough HITs for all participants. Currently I don't really feel all that bad about the situation because it was only a $1 survey.
column30: I think I could reframe the situation by thinking about it as a learning experience. I can think to myself, "Ok, so you forgot about one survey, that's not really the end of the world, you just need to be less forgetful next time and keep track of your priorities better." Thinking about the situation in this way turns it into a situation that I can learn from and it also makes me feel like the situation isn't as negative as it seems and that the situation can be improved, and is not permanent.

column17: I spent some time working on a project and, even though it is something I wanted to be able to do in that it is objectively desirable for me to be working on in certain ways, I have certain negative feelings about it. I don't feel confident that I am necessarily proceeding in the right way. I feel like I might not be working up to my full capacity and that the other party will be displeased because I am not doing my best work. I have the chance to just walk away at this stage, but I feel like I will regret that even more. It does not seem like I will feel like I have done an acceptable job for at least some time after the fact.
column30: The situation will probably be resolved fairly shortly after I choose to fully commit to a course of action, according to what others have told me, so it is fairly temporary in nature. I think things are not so bad because I tend to pretty much always have higher standards for myself compared to others, and I feel like this is no exception. I also do have some experience in performing some fairly similar tasks, so I can use that to my advantage. I just have to power through this and take into account that the absolute worst outcome is really not so bad compared to other problems that I could face.

column17: I had to do a certain workout to keep going with my progress but I skipped it during that day and did not get back to it. This made me feel regret because it should have done it and been consistency with my goals.
column30: The situation while annoying, is probably not as bad as it seems and I can always just do the workout today so that I can get back on track. I can also learn to not skip any more days as they will eventually accumulate.

column17: I drank too much at night and was very upset about it. I am regretting getting drunk
column30: No, i was with my best friends so it's not as negative as i originally thought. No silver lining. I could learn not to drink so much.,

column17: The way my husband's aunt talked down  to me. She has a tend to make me feel  horrible about myself, and yesterday she said some hurtful things. I tend to dwell on what she says often.
column30: I don't think she means those words the way they came out. Some people speak before  think inking and this may be one of those cases. It's just words, so it's not that bad. We won't be living with them forever, so I'll eventually only have to deal with her at family functions.

column17: Yesterday I went hang out with my friends at their house. I had a few beers with them and we got a little bit drunk and the course of our conversation turned to politics. We're somewhat similar in our political views, more or less in the middle though I tend to be a bit more liberal leaning than they are. The conversation got a bit heated in a few places and I got a bit more aggressive in my language than I should have, as well as visibly upset about some of the conversation. I feel like I should have handled the situation better, that I shouldn't let my emotions get the better of me, even when drinking.
column30: I think that the situation will ultimately be fine; we parted as friends and no one was really that upset or angry about anything. The silver lining would be that I know my friendships are strong and we can handle adversity, we have many times in the past. I really think that I could learn how to control my feelings better, or at least, thats what I tell myself. The situation was temporal, but I would like to think that my self-control can be improved. At least I like to think that it can be.

column17: My 2 year old son awoke me out of bed in the middle of the night crying. His crying had scared his brother awake who responded in kind by crying as well. I found my 2 year old on the floor by his bedroom door. I had recently began shutting off the hallway light that he had previously used to find me in my bedroom. He had had a bad dream and wasn't able to put himself back to sleep. I felt bad because I wasn't there for him when he needed me.
column30: Bad dreams are common for young children they probably react more negatively to them because they are still a relatively new experience for them. I'm searching for a solution to the hallway lighting issue that doesn't involve using electricity all night like a motion sensor light perhaps. This situation is in no way permanent. My son has not mentioned that he is troubled much by bad dreams so this is not something that I expect to happen often.

column17:
We have neighbors moving in,they started moving in on Monday. They have a tiny dog named Lady
Lady got out of her carrier and was hit by a car Tuesday morning,I was talking to my new neighbor when it happened. It was shocking,Lady died. My neighbor is devastated! I am so sad for her. She has no children and considered Lady to be her baby. She cant stop crying and I dont know what to do for her. I cant help but feel if I had not been there talking to her,it wouldn't have happened.
column30: This is a permanent situation.I dont see a silver lining right now,the only one I can think of is she will adopt a shelter dog,and give her love to it. That would make her,and the new dog very happy

column17: I developed a break out of acne on my chin this morning. It makes me feel bad about the way I look, because it looks like some kind of rash. I feel like I am too old to be having acne. This one actually hurts my skin because it is below the surface, so I can feel it when I talk. I am annoyed because just when I think my skin has cleared up, it happens again. I want to look the best I can, but there is nothing I can really do about this. I just wish I didn't have bad skin.
column30: I guess it is not really the end of the world. Acne has come and gone for me ever since I was a teenager. It is not permanent, and it seems to be less frequent as I get older. Lots of people my age still get acne breakouts. No one is really looking at it as much as I think they are. There are people with far worse things happening than an acne breakout, I am just being dramatic. Looks are not even important, and a little bit of acne doesn't make me look "disgusting" or anything, no one is thinking that.

column17: Trying to sell my house and talking to people online and no one has come to view it yet. I need to sell it soon so I can move to another location where I am buying another house. I am stressed about if things will work out at all or if there will be any big or small problems before I can get resettled
column30: I am going to find a house quickly in the new area and it will go smoothly and not be too expensive and I will come back here and get all my things in one trip and take it all down there and move in and it will be fast and easy. I can't wait.

column17: Yesterday at work was very frustrating. My job allows me to be the point of contact for my clients at my company. I have to work with my different departments in order to resolve issues. I have had multiple escalations with one client regarding one different department. The client is upset and is losing faith in us. No one responds to my emails or phone calls including the supervisors. I called the supervisor 3 times yesterday without any response. I finally got an email this morning. This is making my job difficult and it frustrates me.
column30: As upsetting as this is, sadly it is part of my job. I have to deal with issues and work through some of these problems. I learned in escalations like these it is better to walk down a few flight of stairs and talk to the people. I think that might help. Hopefully by opening up barriers of communication we can fix this over time.

column17: I was very stressed out because I had to drive a long distance for work. It was an all day drive to make it to another site. I don't like driving that long especially between large metropolitan regions. So I needed to take a deep breath and mentally prepare myself for the long drives.
column30: I think I could use the opportunity as a learning experience to get better at dealing with negative emotions. I also think if I treat it as an opportunity I will feel better overall. And it was over with quickly just a day.

column17: Yesterday, when I went to the gym I only was able to achieve about 60% of my normal workout. This was the second time in a week that this had happened. I feel lacking in energy and drive, and when I don't hit my fitness goal, I feel weak. It's just one of the few things that I have, and one of the few "highs" I look forward to.
column30: Realistically the length and activity level that I achieved would be considered very good and desirable by most people. I did a full hour of cardio, which is sufficient and a healthy behavior. I compensated by the miles I did not run yesterday, by running locally today, when I normally would not have exercised. I actually think it would benefit me to spread out my exercise schedule. I do not have or need any weight loss goals, I exercise purely for health and enjoyment, and I have faith that I can accept the ups and downs. I know I am in the best shape of my life, and my body reflects that.

column17: I had a few drinks at the bar in the evening on Monday evening. After this I went to meet my Mother for dinner at a local restaurant. She brought up issues surrounding my nephew and my brother which sent me on a bit of a tirade about how they need to stop enabling them. Then we got into issues of the problems that would arise for her if anything happened to my father due to his lack of a will. I feel like I was pretty harsh and somewhat regret the interaction.
column30: It's not as negative as it seems we've had similar conversations before about my brother. I try not to berate her, but she gets herself in bad situations with him and I want to see it stop. There are silver linings. She told me this morning that she and my father are going to get a will drawn up for him leaving everything to her so my brother shouldn't be able to screw things up with intestate. The will situation already seems to be. So my mother should be protected. The brother situation will likely improve when he gets caught stealing things again and is back in jail.

column17: I saw a dead dog on the side of the highway. I love dogs, so this has stuck in my mind.
column30: It doesn't matter in the grand scheme of things. I just felt sorry for the dog. The silver lining is at least it wasn't a dog I knew. I guess I learned to keep your pets far away from the highway. Yes, death is fairly permanent.

column17:
My daughter was outside, trying to watch the hummingbirds approach the feeder.  My son kept coming outside and making noise (he's 4) even after I kept telling him to stay inside.  This resulted in everyone getting upset because #1 no hummingbirds were coming #2 I had to yell #3 no one got their way. 

My feelings were frustration because he wasn't listening. then I felt guilty because he is little and still learning.
column30: The situation isn't very negative.  This is every day life for me.  It's full of frustrating times with the kids.  A silver lining would maybe be to teach him how to listen a little better and stay still so he can see the hummingbirds.  I could learn to be a little more patient or try to think of different ways to tell him to go inside.  The situation is temporary.

column17: My son told me yesterday that he wants to stay in another state and not return home this week as had been the plan.  I don´t at all feel badly about myself regarding it, but I feel very disappointed, and a loss of his presence in our home.  I had anticipated and wanted him here with us, attending the local college.  I don´t feel he´s necessarily doing the wrong thing, but it´s not what I wish for him.  Every time I think of it I feel badly, regretful, like the situation is out of order.  I want to do something to change it, but I know it´s not mine to change.  My feelings are basically concern, and disappointment, and loss.
column30: He is in another state earning 1.5 x what he´d earn if here.  He will have a sizable amount of money,  He´s being safe, having independence and adventure,  He wasn't particularly happy here so if he's happy there I'm glad for him.  The situation isn't permanent.  It's just not what I want.  It has been a great opportunity to demonstrate to him that I will support him in what he wants and decides even when it's not what I want for him and he knows it's not.  So he's experiencing that he can choose apart from what primary others want and it's still ok and he's still respected.

column17: I got in a fight with a friend last night over politics.  We always get into it over them and I guess we haven't learned our lesson yet.  Its nothing really major or anything, and we get over it pretty quickly, but sometimes I worry that one of these days something might get said that could have potential consequences.
column30: It's nothing really major that we can't settle quickly.  Its healthy to have disagreements once in a while to test the friendship.  We make it through stronger.

column17: My dog, which is 2.5 y/o but I just got earlier this year, I suspect she is not potty trained and has been urinating on furniture lately. She had urinated on my bed twice and on my couch once. It is very upsetting, but I'm starting to deal with it. I have made an appointment to take her in to the vet on Friday to see if it has a medical reason (urinary tract or bladder infection) or if it is a behavioral problem. I have been working extra hard to make sure to watch her and praise her when she does go outside to do her business and there haven't been anymore accidents since the last one, but it still has me on edge since I have to watch her constantly.
column30: Like I said, I am going to take her to the vet on Friday so I will know how to proceed. I'm trying to be as positive as possible about the situation because I have read that dogs can sense your emotions and if you are upset with them it can make the behavior worse (if it is a behavioral problem). I am focusing on positive reinforcement and so far I think it is working, but it hasn't been very long since her last accident. I guess a silver lining is that if this is a medical problem I will be able to take care of it soon and then I wont have to worry about her urinating on things anymore. I am learning a lot from the internet about dog behavior problems and how to properly potty train them, so that will help make it easier in the future if I have to potty train a new dog. I think this situation is temporary, even if she isn't potty trained. You can teach an older dog, it is probably just more difficult.

column17: Just yesterday I got prescribed some Antibiotics for my Urinary Infection. I've been stressing slightly about whether they will work effitivelely. I started searching around the internet about peoples success with this antibiotic type and it just made my head worse. I wish I could just stop feeling like this. I regret ever searching for symptoms and crap on the internet, just go to the doctor as soon as you can.
column30: I managed to get my Antiotictics from the doctor to treat my urinary infection yesterday. I'm slightly worried about the effectiveness. The situation is better because I went to the doctor but I still get worried. Maybe from all of this, I could finally start learning my lesson and stop trying to be a doctor, just visit my doctor once I feel something is wrong.

column17: I went to three movies with a friend. I took the aisle seat even though I knew she would have liked it. I felt bad about that.
column30: I went to the movies with a friend. I took the aisle seat so I wouldn't have to climb over her to go to the bathroom.

column17: I am stressed because I had a fight with my husband. We just found out he has a hernia in his groin and he's pretty worried about it. I am not the most sympathetic person, and I pretty much told him to man up. I feel bad, because I really hurt his feelings.
column30: I have learned that I need to be more compassionate and understanding with my husband. I never realized how much he frets over things and I have learned that I need to be a support to him, and not to criticize him. This will help our relationship going forward.

column17: A couple of days ago, I was sending a check to my mom, who I owed some money, and while doing this a huge wave of guilt took over me. I felt guilty for all the money my parents have helped me with, so guilty, in fact, that it interfered with my concentration, causing me to mess the envelop and have to start with a fresh one. I still feel guilty about it, because I still owe them a lot of money.
column30: The situation really isn't as negative as it seems. My parents wouldn't have helped me if they didn't love me, so I have to look at it from that perspective. There could be a silver lining in this situation, I just haven't seen it yet. I can definitely gain something useful from this. This situation can allow me to feel gratitude, not only to my parents, but to all of the people who have helped me throughout my life. The situation can improve as my financial situation improves. But every time I think about it, I feel guilty. I have to learn how to get over my guilt first.

column17: This time I had a new car in mind , I had done all the research , read all the reports .. the Mercedes was the car for me. I went to the dealer picked out the car ....Then the bad news .. a ding on my credit report and I can't get the car. My world was ruined I could not get the car I wanted and I just didn't know what to do. I thought about lowering myself to driving an Italian or British car but the thought of either was just too much to deal with .
column30: This time I had a new car in mind , I had done all the research , read all the reports .. the Mercedes was the car for me. I went to the dealer picked out the car ....Then the bad news .. a ding on my credit report and I can't get the car. My world was ruined I could not get the car I wanted and I just didn't know what to do. I thought about lowering myself to driving an Italian or British car but the thought of either was just too much to deal with .

column17: I had a fight with a friend yesterday. It was something very small and now it has even grown bigger issue. I feel a bit bad for my friend. My current feeling right now is more to calm and rethink what went so wrong.
column30: Arguing with a friend sometimes give me a negative impact. What I could learn from this situation is next time I would have to try to listen first before talking. This situation is temporary. Time will heal and improve it.

column17: Someone in my family is having health problems and I'm concerted about this. I'm not quite sure what's wrong with them and don't want to pry, but they have a chronic condition that sometimes flares up and I'm concerned it has something to do with that. I'm worried that they might deteriorate sometime in the near future. When/if this happens, they might be in a period of rather poor health for several weeks/days, I'd imagine - I've only seen this happen to them once, I think, and it was quite difficult for everyone in the family.
column30: There's really not much I can do to fix the situation, so I really only can focus on my feelings. I just have to help this person if something is wrong with them. This flare-up might only be temporary, though unfortunately, the condition is permanent. And, of course, there is always the possibility that the issue is totally unrelated to their chronic condition. I feel like there is a decent chance that this is indeed actually the case, and that they might not want to talk about this for other reasons.

column17: Yesterday, my husband came home from work and he was pretty down. He had a horrible day at the office. It makes upset. When he started this job, he was over the moon. His emotions tend to rub off on me, so I was feeling concerned for him. Eventually while we talked about what happened in the day to make him feel that way, I started to feel a little blue myself.
column30: The situation wasn't that bad. I texted my husband at work today, and he seemed to turn the bad day yesterday into a great day today so far. So the situation has been improved.

column17: I realized I have very little money left until pay day next week.  This bothers me as I can't do anything extra and have to be careful with food and gas purchases.  The water bill due in a few days will be tricky.
column30: This is a good lesson in saving each pay period and not getting carried away when I have extra money.  It's a cycle I'm on and I think this is a very good learning experience to be more smart with money at all times.

column17: In the past two days I had a fight with a friend over their attitude towards me. It made me feel bad to have the fight but I felt like I had to speak out because I didn't feel like I should be treated like that and that helped the situation in the long term.
column30: I think that I needed to have the disagreement in order to try and improve the relationship in the long term. Because now perhaps things will get better and there will be more respect.

column17: The situation I am thinking about involves an interaction with a prospective client that was a bit frustrating. They were extraordinarily vague about what they wanted, and despite multiple attempts to clarify, I was mostly unsuccessful. I walked away feeling very frustrated due to the amount of time/energy and patience exerted, while essentially feeling as though I accomplished next to nothing & ultimately be left to divine whatever it is they want on my own if I want the job. I'm still quite irritated.
column30: The situation is probably not as negative as it seems. The reality is that I can only do as much as I can do with the information I have, and the rest is not really up to me. I will have made my best effort. The only silver lining is that if I choose to do nothing at all/walk away, that's ultimately ok too. I really don't know what there is to learn from the situation, as sometimes clients are just extraordinarily hard to deal with -- that will not change. I suppose, if anything, I could learn to let it bother me less, and focus on the fact that it is excruciatingly little, if anything, to do with me, and nearly everything to do with them. The situation is not permanent by any means, and will likely improve one way or another.

column17: I spent all day making a cake for my children's birthday party and they made a huge mess in the process.  I'm pretty mad because I've been desperately trying to keep the house clean, bake, shop and prepare for the party and they are old enough to clean up after themselves.  They know how to put things away and where they belong, but they still do it.
column30: It's not very negative, I just am tired and need them to pitch in.  The silver lining is that I probably won't make their cake again because it's such a pain in the ass. I can't really gain much from the situation - they are grounded now and will be cleaning and reading until the party, or playing outside.  The situation isn't permanent and it is improving.

column17: My niece and nephew came over to stay the night because my sister is in the hospital after giving birth. They're very loud and kind of obnoxious, and it sort of ruins the atmosphere that I'm used to because I really enjoy a quiet house and being able to hear myself think. I'm currently not really that annoyed because they will be living soon, but I'm kind of disappointed in myself for having such a reaction, although it's not unusual as I don't really like kids.
column30: I guess I could reframe this event as a way for me to bond with my niece and nephew and try to work on my patience, and work on my ability to be an effective uncle. The situation probably isn't that negative as it isn't permanent and they will be leaving soon. I can certainly gain some perspective in this situation and learn how to better interact with children in such a way to have them listen to me and to make myself not as annoyed by their presence, that way I will feel better in future interactions.

column17: My husband had a wisdom tooth extraction at the end of last week. In the past couple of days, my husband has complained of achiness and pain that I just brushed off as a normal part of the healing process. Today, my husband went for a checkup with his dentist and it turns out that he had a massive infection. He's currently under the knife to drain the infection and I feel very badly for not having really believed him about how he felt.
column30: My husband didn't even know his problem was this severe so it's understandable that I didn't know either. After this procedure, my husband should be on the road to recovery and will get better rather than worse. I learned that I still need to listen a little more closely when people tell me how they feel and to not take anything anyone says for granted. Just a few more days of my husband recovering from surgery and everything should be once again back to normal.

column17: An event that took place in the past two days that still bothers me is when I went to a local liquor store. During this time I went with some friends to get something to make some mixed drinks. During this time there was someone in the store who appeared to be drunk and wanted to argue and start a problem with us.My current thoughts and feelings about this is that I felt bad that my friends had to put up with this and I felt bad that I could not make this person stop and had to deal with it also.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because no one was hurt and we were able to get out of the situation fairly quickly. There are not really any silver linings that I can think of, but I am sure that there is some that I just can not see or experience yet. I could learn that I am a very calm and emotionally put together person.I can help other people to remain calm in tense situations and not do something dangerous. This situation is not permanent because no one is really thinking or talking about it other than me. This situation can not really improve, but I feel that it can be forgotten and not really have any effect on people.

column17: It's small but it's the only thing I can think of.  I have 2 pairs of shorts that are a good brand and they were 5.00 each.  I didn't take the time to try them on in the store.  I got the size I thought was right (they are actually mens' but I like how mens' fit better) but I found them to be TOO roomy and comfortable.  I decided I would use a belt, but got lazy and usually just wear them without.  They sag so badly they could literally fall off.  They are very roomy in the legs and hips and I find it nice wearing something that's not constricting.  Well, for the first time I saw myself in a full-length mirror in them and somehow they add about 40 pounds.  Not 5 or 10.  They are huge and make me seem to really be as large as they are and it's not flattering.  So.....  I feel badly in retrospect for all the times, including yesterday, that I ran errands around town maybe not thinking I was the epitome of style but I didn't know I was looking HORRIBLE.  Why didn't my kids tell me???
column30: Although it's just shorts.......I feel badly somehow.  I always wear these shorts with shirts that made pleasing color combinations and I felt good in the outfits.  Now I see that how I presented myself to others wasn't how I was perceiving myself and I don't like what I presented.  I actually don't mind "big" or "large" at all as a size for humans.  Fat isn't really bad in my mind.  Yet for me, when I see myself looking really large and bulky I don't like it.  No, it's not significant or important in any way.  I guess mainly I'm disappointed for the future as those 2 shorts will have to never again leave the house and they were roomy and comfy.  Silver linings or ways to re-frame?  Probably that others didn't see me that way, negatively, but probably more responded to how I carried myself and my energy, and I was feeling good so probably projected that.  Also, I need to put up a mirror where I can check my outfit each day.  I used to ALWAYS do that and lost habit somehow.

column17: I had a big client meeting and the team that was supposed to prepare me, didn't tlel me. It went really poorly and i feel really bad about myself
column30: It wasn't my fault and the team wasn't super helpful. They already like me so it wasn't much skin off of my back. It can be improved next demo!

column17: My brother and my mom have been arguing about politics on facebook, and it is kind of annoying and ruins the family harmony. I have to try to be the peacekeeper and make sure nothing too bad is said. I feel like I shouldn't have to deal with something so dumb and that they are both adults. It makes my family look bad to anyone else who follows them. It makes me feel like I am from a trashy family.
column30: I can look at this situation and realize it doesn't affect my life as much as I think it does. What my family does is on them, I am an adult. I can learn from what I see, and realize how things come across online. I know the fighting will be over eventually and things will calm down again. We will get along. I should just look at the funny side of it.

column17: I had a stressful meeting at a cancer center today.I had to go and see a doctor,do some paperwork,and schedule an appointment with a surgeon to remove a lump in my left breast. They say its benign,but contains pre~ cancer cells.Its a bit depressing,but I guess it could always be worse.
column30: This situation will improve.Although it is very negative,it does have  a silver lining. I will have it removed. Although it does contain pre cancer cells,the doctor says MOST tumors with pre cancer cells never develop into cancer.It could have been so much worse. I could have actually had cancer . I feel blessed.

column17: This morning, before my son went to school, I yelled at him. It was pretty bad. I shouldn't have done that, I should have waited until after school to talk to him about why I was angry, but I didn't.
column30: This situation was negative, but it can make me more aware in the future to hold my tongue and be patient.

column17: Earlier today I accidentally sat a hot pot down on our kitchen table without a trivet beneath it and melted a big hole in our tablecloth cover. I was really trying not to cause any trouble today because I've been really on edge for the past few days in dealing with my family. I was trying to do something nice and make breakfast for them but I messed that up too by destroying our tablecloth cover and making a mess of things. I feel like an awful person, like I can't do anything right. I'm not very nice to people and when I try to be nice I just end up screwing things up even more. I feel like a failure of a person who can't even do basic things right.
column30: I guess in the longrun its not a big deal. I doubt my family is going to abandon me for something like that. They've known who I am and how useless and terrible I am for years now and I doubt that one more screw-up is really going to change things. While I was told not to think of things I can do to change the situation, its worth mentioning that I can buy a new tablecloth cover and I have done so... so the situation isn't a permanent one. Doing so made me spend money I really didn't intend to spend and was put me more in a bind money-wise than I was before but I think its worth it. I know the situation isn't permanent and it can be improved. Mostly my thoughts now are on being more careful in the future.

column17: My microwave broke, and I can't afford to buy a new one for about the next two weeks.
column30: It's annoying that I can't heat things up with the microwave. The oven takes longer. I don't know what I would gain or learn from this, except buy a new microwave when the old one craps out.

column17: For certain components of my job, I/we frequently have routine audits, or spot checks, to ensure that work is accurate, timely, and consistent with correct procedure. While I didn't "fail" mine yesterday, I didn't do well by my standards.  What is most frustrating is I am not specifically told what I was incorrect on....at least not right away.  My position depends on being able to always meet performance measurements and there is not a lot of job security. So I am frustrated by not understanding my errors, and I get anxiety about the ease with which I could lose my job. I think that after two years of mostly repetitive work, I would have it down pat. But these unsatisfactory audits have been popping up more often than I'm comfortable with and I dont' know what my problem is. I feel incompetent and agitated.
column30: I become stagnate, complacent and less observant about my work, as it becomes so habitual. I need to become aware of bad habits and repetitive errors before they become worse. I also need to stay current on updates, as guidelines change with frequency in the tech world. Also, my performance was still acceptable, by organizational standards. So this is just me being hard on myself.

column17: I ended up going into work on my day off. That was enough to stress me out, but my one client has started to escalate almost everything. There was one project were working on. It is very routine and she normally works directly with our stocks department. However, she was escalating routine orders to me. She was complaining about our slow turnaround time. The turnaround times are the standard times that have been communicated to her before. This forces me to have to reach out to management for routine operations. She has expressed her disappointment with our company and the service. This looks bad for me and makes me anxious and on edge.
column30: This is an annoying situation, but not has bad as it seems. I usually cool things over with this client and we have a good relationship. I just dislike the extra attention from management that is not really needed. Something we can do better is working on interdepartmental communication so we can be on the same page. We are doing a lot better with that and I am building relationships in those departments. I believe the personality for my client will not change. She will do this, but we can do a better job of being on the same page and resolve things quicker.

column17: My dog has been having accidents on furniture. I have to keep her in her crate now pretty much whenever I cannot be watching her. I don't think she minds but it still upsets me that she can't just hangout around the house with my other dog, but I cannot deal with constantly cleaning up messes. I took her to the vet today to find out if it is a medical reason (UTI) or if it is a behavioral problem. They took urine and are going to do a urinalysis, but I will not know results until Monday. They also wanted to do bloodwork, but I cannot afford it and figured it wasn't as necessary since she had bloodwork done in April and it came back normal. It makes me feel guilty, like I'm not doing what she needs but I'm doing everything that I can. I don't know what I'm going to do if it comes back normal and it turns out to be a behavioral problem. I've read all that I can about it, and am doing everything that is suggested, but she still has accidents. I don't want to give up on her, so maybe I will have to save up for a behaviorist to help me.
column30: I guess I am getting ahead of myself since I wont know the results until Monday. I shouldn't worry about it until I know what the results are and I can probably talk with my vet about what my options are. I hope I can learn something to help my dog from the vet either way because I don't know where to begin to look for someone to help if it is a behavior problem. I am in hopes that this is a temporary problem since I've only had her since April, and if she doesn't have a UTI that I can get her properly potty trained so she doesn't have to be in her crate all the time.

column17: I woke up later than I wanted to and had to make less money on that day.
column30: While I may have woken up late and missed some money on that day, it helps remind me that I can do better and to focus more so that I can accomplish more each day.

column17: Something that stressed me out in the past few days is that I had to sit behind someone going slow when I was driving and I could not go around them. This annoyed me because this person was going unusually slow and well below the speed limit. I thought angry words in my head and I wanted to punch this person in the face even though I would never act on that feeling. I was annoyed because I hate when I am powerless to do anything about stupid people on the road.
column30: It is okay because I still got to my destination on time. The situation is not as negative as it seems because the driver that was going too slow pays taxes to use the road how he wants to use it just like me. The silver lining to the situation is that my anger is more of a reflection on me than it is on the other driver and I am grateful to learn this lesson. I learned that it is not worth getting mad over things that do not matter in the long run. The situation is not permanent because I will not run into that person again and I am living comfortably in my house.

column17: I had to stay over at my sister's place because of things going on im my life right now and I feel that I wore out my welcome and I got into an argument with my brother in law. He doesn't want me staying there anymore, and he gets upset at my sister when she agrees to let me stay with them.  My brother in law and I got into a little spat and I ended up staying at a hotel.
column30: The situation might spur me in order to get my life together so I don't have to rely on other people to get things done.

column17: I am trying to sell my house and it didn't sell it this week. Hopefully next week.  I feel stressed out because there is a lot of things I have to do to move and sell this house
column30: I am going to sell this house pretty fast I believe. It has some good points to it and I think someone will buy it pretty fast.  It will go smoothly and all the paperwork will go easily and then it will be over very fast and I will be out of here in very short time.

column17: My Mom asked me what my plans were for Christmas. This is stressful for me because I can't plan that far ahead.
column30: My Mom asked me what my plans were for Christmas. This got me thinking about all the family I get to see and it made me happy.

column17: I was contacted the other day in regards to an inquiry that I had made about market research project that I had participated in at the end of June. Now after waiting patiently for six weeks for payment, I reached out to him to have him tell me that I would have to wait another four weeks because the survey was in his words, "very complex" - which it was not. It was similar to this one where I was asked to complete a survey every day where I would be asked the same question. So after being told that I was going to be paid in four to eight weeks, he tacked on another two weeks. This made me really wonder if he was stalling me because he couldn't pay me for some reason. So you could imagine how pissed off I was and still am.
column30: Right now, this situation really is as negative as it seems. I did the work, and now am being given the runaround about being paid. I truthfully cannot see any silver lining in this situation. The only useful thing I can gain is to be more cautious from now on about who I do surveys for, and that may not be helpful in the long run if I miss out on something because of being overly cautious. The only way the situation can be improved is if he pays me, but that's not going to take away the feeling I have of being used by this company.

column17: I burned my while cooking last night. I saw the food fly over to the ceiling. I am not exaggerating. I feel bad because technically I was wasting a lot of unedible food at the end. Even now I still feel very negative about it.
column30: Well, actually this situation is not that bad. I am just bad at cooking maybe. The next time I would just use the microwave to cook something. I would start by using a simple recipe. Anything can be learned from the Internet. I think I can improve my cooking. At least, I know now don't put the whole steak in the deep fryer!

column17: I spent went out on Sunday and spent far more than I meant to. I had a good time and my bar tab itself wasn't too bad. However I spent $15 on the gambling machine and had a burger instead of eating at home. I also smoked too many cigarettes and I've been trying to cut down. Not only am I a bit hungover today, but I feel like I have to work an extra day to make up for the spending. I feel bad about not having proper self control.
column30: It's not the end of the world. I had a particularly good day today and have more than made the money I spent yesterday. I did get to hang out with my friends. I need to be more careful when I go out, I'm used to being considerably more well off than I am at the moment, but I'm getting better about it. It's by no means a permanent situation.

column17: A source of stress for me was a financial situation where I had to suddenly worry about facing steep penalties for an issue that I was ultimately responsible for.
column30: The negative seemed very distressing due to the steep fees. I knew that I could resolve it but I would have to do it quickly. I can learn to not put myself in this situation again.

column17: I feel like I have been going out of my way to maintain and take care of a space of mine and certain things in it, but it does not seem as if my efforts are working. I am doing everything I can to keep the space and what's in it clean and organized, but it does not seem as if it gets better. It seems like it is the same regardless of whether or not I make an effort. It annoys me to put time and effort into something that does not seem to be yielding any dividends.
column30: No one else is really that concerned about the situation other than me, so I am not really letting anyone down by how I perform here. Perhaps there are some new things I could try that I have not already tried. There are some large changes I have been thinking about making but have not so perhaps it is time to try one of those. It is possible that incremental positive changes are occurring in the situation but I just have not noticed them yet, as it is a bit hard for me to objectively assess this situation.

column17: My husband is back from surgery but is his energy and motivation level is suffering as a result of the medication he's on. This morning I finally blew off some steam by telling him that I was struggling to care for our kids and home on my own. I could tell that I instantly that I had made him feel guilty and we didn't speak to one another for the rest of the morning.
column30: Honestly, this altercation is just as ordinary as any other disagreement that we've had. Also, being honest finally with my husband will help us open up to further communication on the subject. I think experiencing the struggle that I've been having will help me to take my husband less for granted in the long run. My husband will eventually be off of his medications and will be able to help me with the kids and housework again in no time.

column17: My family wanted to have something different for dinner last night so they decided to do a crab boil. Unfortunately I don't like crab (It tastes ok, but I don't like how it looks and I hate having to fight with it) so I didn't eat any of it. I felt bad that they had gone out of their way to get food for me that I didn't like. I feel guilty that I didn't eat any of the food they got for me and I feel ungrateful. I'm a little bit resentful, truth be told. I know it sounds silly, but I resent being put into positions like that too. Where I have to either make myself suffer or come off like an a-hole. It's another reminder, even if in a small way, that I'm not much like the other people in my life.
column30: Honestly the situation isn't as negative as I imagine it to be. I don't think anyone is actually upset and no one's said any cross words to me. I guess by now my family knows who I am and won't be disowning me over something so minor. I guess in the end I know it doesn't really matter, it was a minor thing. I'm an adult and I don't need to depend on anyone else for my meals. I suppose I learned that I should communicate better with my family and express the things that I like and dislike a little bit more. I don't guess this specific situation is permanent, but feeling different from my family and feeling like they don't understand me might very well be. These odd feelings of guilt and isolation over minor things in my life might be permanent. I don't really know.

column17: I was invited to a family reunion and I flat out refused to go. I feel bad because I won't get to see my uncle, but there's no way in hell I'm going because I refuse to breathe the same air as a few of the rest of them.
column30: I could make myself remember that I told my uncle goodbye back in 1995 so there's no need to show up now to do it again because he's dying.

column17: I was stressed out yesterday because I thought I wasn't going to be able to reach my daily goal on MTurk that I set for myself, and I was worried that I wouldn't make enough money, and I was worried that the overall state of MTurk might be declining. Currently I don't feel bad as I know that the overall state isn't really declining all that much, if at all.
column30: I think I can reframe the situation by trying to tell myself that it's better to go with the flow of things instead of possibly overreacting about a situation when you don't even know all the details. I think the situation certainly wasn't as negative as I thought initially, and I could learn to be more realistic and rational in such moments, instead of getting emotional. The situation also can certainly improve, so there was no real reason to get so upset in the first place, I just needed to change my frame of mind.

column17: I texted a guy that i like and he didn't respond. I am feeling sad and rejected.
column30: No, he could have just been busy. He also could not be for me.

column17: I spent too much money and realized I have until today to pay my water bill.  I had an extension for today, but only have 12 dollars in my account.  They are pretty aggressive in shutting off water for non payment so I paid it with an e check an now my account is overdrawn until Friday.
column30: I've learned to go back to paying my bills first.  After paying bills, put some money in savings then what is left is what I can spend.  I've been in a tough financial situation since my divorce and bankruptcy and I need to geed back on track.  This is an eye opener to be smart and understand every dollar counts.

column17: I actually had a pretty upsetting conversation with my sister today. I'm not terribly comfortable relaying the intimate details, but it essentially left me feeling varying degrees of worried for the situation she is in coupled with layers of guilty for not doing anything to help her out more, as well as attempting to be firm in my advice (as well as the advice I gave her from the outset, which would likely have precluded the situation she finds herself in now). Overall, it's just frustrating and concerning.
column30: At the moment, yes, I think it's fair to say the situation is as negative as it seems. The only notable silver lining is that she is still talking about the issues versus attempting to hide them. Given that I've already gone through the particular life lesson she seems intent on learning the hard way, I think the only real useful takeaway for me is to work more on accepting her for exactly who she is & being ok with that. I genuinely have no idea how permanent the situation will be -- with regard to my outlook, it will improve with either time, or a concerted effort at changing the way I'm processing my emotions about it -- likely both.

column17: I felt a little left out this weekend. I didn't get to do as much with the people I normally am with on the weekend. When I feel left out, it makes me feel a little down. Being not included sucks sometimes, especially when it's family that excludes you.
column30: There's always next weekend. So hopefully we'll be able to do stuff then. It's not a permanent exclusion, so it'll be fine.

column17: I feel guilty about taking time off to play a video game that just launched a new expansion.  Instead of going to work I stayed home and played world of warcraft.  And that's not acceptable at my age.
column30: It's pretty negative because rent is due soon. But I did have a lot of fun. My acting so irresponsibly is pretty permanent though.

column17: Surprisingly I found out that I have to move out soon, it got me all stressed even tho it wasn't a big deal. I've been getting ready for the past 4 months and I'm almost ready. This still makes me feel stressed because I hate change, I like the way things are now but nothing I can do about it at this point.
column30: Finding out I have to move out in the near future, been getting ready for it but it still sucks. The situation is not as bad as it seems tho, I will be better off in my new place and getting used to it will happen naturally. Although I'm already used to things the way they are right now, it's just not worth staying in my current place, things will stay the same if I stay at my current place but maybe they can improve when I move out.

column17: My sister in law was recently diagnosed with liver failure,and needs to be put on a transplant list.She was told her best chances were for a live donor.I cant be tested because of my heart condition.That makes me sad. She is going through so much right now. I had no idea the liver controlled that much of the human body. Her son was asked yesterday to be tested,and he said,NO...I couldnt believe it!! I am so angry with him right now.
column30: The situation is as negative as it sounds. I try to feel better about it by thinking that her son will change his mind and just be tested to be a donor,now that he has found out he is going to be a father

column17: Well, this is a physical thing that bothers me:  I got a burn and while it's healed pretty well and quickly (today is day 11) out of nowhere it's itchy/red/bumpy where yesterday it was smooth.  It's like it's got hives. I thought it would heal with no scar but out of nowhere today -it's bumpy and look like it will scar in a raised bumpy manner.  And it itches and feels badly so it's been stressing me out all day.
column30: It's not permanent.  I don't know if I can learn anything or find a silver lining.  I'm glad it didn't get infected, I didn't need a skin graft so I'm grateful for those things. I guess I'm glad it wasn't a burn on my face or something.  I already did learn when it occurred what NOT to do so it doesn't happen again.  But learning something in the past 2 days....or finding something positive in it in the recent time....probably not except that it's healing, it will get better.

column17: An event that took place in the past two days that still bothers me is when I was talking to a friend on the phone and they made a smart remark about something I said. During this time I was talking to them about something that I was hoping to achieve in the near future. They kind of blew me off and made a noise that sounded like they did not believe me. This made me feel bad because I thought I could trust them and they would make me feel like I could achieve and do something great, but instead they made me feel stupid and like I was making things up.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because it is possible that I just misunderstood or did not react to the situation right. I think that it is not as negative because they could of just been in a bad mood. There is not any silver linings that I could think of, but I am sure that they are there. I could learn something in this situation such as not to overreact to small things that someone says or does. I do not know what type of day they were having or if they were just busy so they reacted in that way. The situation is not permanent because my friend is not going to care or think about it at all. I also feel that in the next few days no one is going to care or think about it except me.

column17: I was playing basketball barefoot, which is dumb, and I stubbed my toe really bad on the ground. It was a dumb careless mistake. I have a basketball game coming up and now I know I won't be able to play as well as I should. I feel like I am letting my friends down a bit, even though it is not a serious game. I feel like I shouldn't be doing dumb stuff like this at my age. I feel like other people think I am careless at times and need to be more responsible.
column30: I think the situation isn't a big deal if I take a bigger perspective. The toe will heal, it's not broken. I need to take this as an opportunity to stop making dumb mistakes, and take care of my body better. I feel like my team will be fine without me playing at top speed, i'm a shooter anyway. Also I have an excuse to relax and watch TV tonight instead of work on a yard project I don't really want to do today, that is one positive.

column17: Today was a very stressful day at work. On one of my accounts, I work with an account manager. She was recently just hired to the company. She is a super nice lady, but is not ready for this position. I was frustrated because she started doing some of my work and messed it up.
