This forced me to have to advise the client we made an error. It was upsetting that she did not get the necessary training in order to do her job. I am starting to worry that my job responsibilities my start to overlap with hers.
column30: This situation isn't too bad. I really just need to allow her time to learn her role. It will be difficult for me since her role is a pay grade ahead of mine. It is not really my job to teach her, but I will try to assist in any way that I can. This will make me look good, which is nice. I will be able to learn a bit about her role, which will help in my role in the long run. I do not expect this to be permanent as she hopefully grow into her role.

column17: In the past couple of days I got into a disagreement with a family member which caused some stress. It was stressful because it was a big disagreement and we haven't been able to completely work it out yet. Now I am worried about when we can work it out.
column30: I think that I could work on feeling better without necessarily relying on this external event to change my mood maybe there are other things I can focus on that could make me feel better regardless of how this argument turns out.

column17: I went to a best buy to try to cash in a gift card for another item in the store.  When I went to the checkout the guy told me that I couldn't buy what I wanted with my gift card because their computer couldn't do that sort of transaction.  So now I'm stuck with a gift card that I can't use for the item that I want.
column30: Maybe there is something else I can buy in the future or maybe I can gift them to someone else instead of having to spend more cash for a present.

column17: My dog started urinating on furniture, so I made an appointment at the vet for last Friday to determine if there was a medical reason or if it is a behavior problem. I started crating her at night (because she peed on the bed) and when I'm not home, so I have made some progress on her not having accidents. When I took her to the vet, they did a urinalysis and an exam. I was frustrated that they didn't really discuss what they thought as far as if it was a medical or behavioral problem, or what I should do, but I figured that I would hear back once they got results from the urinalysis. I got a call on Saturday that they got the results and that she is not drinking enough because it was concentrated and they found crystals in the urine. They wanted me to start a special diet for her and encourage her to drink more. I went in to the vet to get the special diet they want her on, but there were no vets present only techs so they couldn't give me any information on if this could be causing her accidents or if this is a behavioral problem. I bought the food, and fortunately she seems to like it, but I am just really frustrated feeling like I don't have answers and they just want me to spend a lot of money on appointments and this new diet. They want to follow up in a month to see if the diet helps her, and I have to wait until Wednesday when the vet is in again. I guess it is just making me anxious rather than mad/depressed.
column30: The situation isn't that negative, at least I did take her to the vet and am in the process of trying to help her. Even though I didn't want to have to crate her I think it is helping, and I hope this new diet does help her. In the exam they noticed that she had irritation on her hind quarters (she has been obsessively licking) so if it is an allergy maybe the new food could help with that as well. I guess the only thing I feel like I can learn from this situation is to ask more questions when I see the vet so that I'm not feeling anxious. I am pretty sure this situation will be temporary and can improve, it will just take some time.

column17: Work guidelines have been updated/changed, so there is a somewhat new procedure for verifying and reporting which was effected today. This is common, but it always seems to take me forever to become familiar, quick and confident again in my tasks every time there is a change. Co-workers hate it too, but I feel like I have more difficulty processing. Im finding with age I am simply less quick and my mind is less flexible and teachable. Then I start feeling like time is running out and I'm going nowhere, never will advance, and the future is hopeless. Simply because I have to do a routine thing slightly different. Total domino effect.
column30: I have been through this shift and change countless times. I have to be a little more meticulous and careful until I get the procedure down, then it becomes as familiar as the last method. It truly is a minor change, and a typical work annoyance that everybody experiences. I have capitulated the situation drastically in my mind.

column17: An event that took place recently that bothers me is that my cat kept bothering me when I wanted to be left alone the other day. He is too stubborn and wants to play too much. He annoyed me greatly. My current thoughts and feelings is that that is funny. That is cats for you.
column30: The situation is not as negative as it seems. The silver lining to the situation is that I know that if I do not want to ever get annoyed I simply have to get rid of all my pets. I could not gain anything useful from this situation except to realize you will be annoyed when you have pets. The situation is not permanent and can be improved by simply accepting that when you have pets you will be annoyed.

column17: There was a qualification hit on mturk a couple of days ago that missed out on because I thought too little of my abilities. This is something that happens quite often and I'm always upset about it when I see people posting about how much money they're making doing these hits and I feel left out and bummed about the money I'm missing out on. So I feel bad about missing the qual and about allowing myself to do this to myself again. It makes me feel inadequate compared to other turkers.
column30: I'm trying to make this situation not as negative as it seems. I need to grow from this experience and expand myself to try new things without giving up so easily. I need to think higher of myself and be willing to try. The silver lining is that I can always improve myself. I need to start feeling comparing myself to others and think about things that I do have instead of what I don't have. I can improve this situation by continuing to think about my good qualities and stop focusing on the negative.

column17: Nothing has happened to make me feel bad since last time.
column30: It's a moot point, since nothing has happened to make me feel bad since last time.

column17: I cleaned out my kitchen and got many bags full of stuff to give away or throw away and I am getting my house ready to sell. It is very stressful when you have to move because you have no choice. I have very bad neighbors who won't stop harassing and bothering me so I have no choice but to move. I am in my mother's old house and trying to clean it up and find another house and then get all my stuff moved there many miles away is stressful and working also and having to do it all by myself and one of the neighbors is a cop and now they appear to be trying to set me up also.  So it is a very bad situation I am in.
column30: This could be a good thing because I will be getting out of a very bad area with a lot of bad people and meeting new people and having fun probably. I will get a job somewhere and get settled and have a great life.

column17: I went out to dinner with a friend. When it came time to pay I gave the waitress less than I normally do (she was a little rude). I feel badly about this.
column30: I went out to dinner with a friend. I left a tip even though the service wasn't very good.

column17: In the past two days, I felt mentally exhausted with my home. My home currently is a real mess and nobody has not even clean it up.
column30: It is negative because I might get sick from all these germs. Well, I think I will start cleaning up the house tomorrow. It can be improved if I was not lazy to clean the house. I learned that cleaning house is essential. No excuses just because I was mentally exhausted.

column17: I went to my nutritionist and weigh a lot more than expected. I was really unhappy and i still am really stressed.
column30: I am working on it now so it isn't as negative. It can improve if i work hard.

column17: My son expressed sadness about his new school. He misses his old school and friends and teachers there. One of his friends from his old school plays football with him, and he said to me “you took my best friend away”.
column30: It’s a life lesson to learn to deal with change and new situations for him. Maybe it reinforces how much he loved his school and I need to work on getting him back there after my finances get in order.

column17: I am currently concerned/stressed about some certain aspects of my physical environment - I wrote about this before/recently, but will try to focus on other aspects of this problem. The weather seems to have inordinate effects on certain aspects of my physical space and I am worried that it is being damaged, degraded, or depreciated, and that this might affect the resale value or cost me money in other ways. I might move at some point in the future and have certain other financial issues, so losing a lot of money because of natural processes I cannot control is stressful and unpleasant to consider.
column30: I guess the least concerning aspect of this is that I cannot control a lot of it and should thus try to keep that in mind when considering my level of stress. It will also be a problem that will probably be resolved when I move at some point. Other people also might be understanding of this problem as they understand the local weather conditions and how they can affect physical spaces.

column17: I was sitting downstairs working and my brother who's supposedly in rehab came by. He needed money. My dad tried to make him feel bad about taking the money instead of saying no. After they all yelled at each other for a half hour or so he gave him the money. I make sure not to get involved, but I really hate that he does this. Both my brother being terrible and my parents giving in.
column30: The situation isn't quite as negative as I am not directly involved, but it is bad for my parents. The silver lining is that it is almost inevitable that he will be back in jail sooner than later. I'm not sure what I can learn not to be awful I guess. It will improve eventually. At some point soon I will move out of here and will only have to hear about him second hand.

column17: The only thing that comes to mind is a conversation with my (deeply republican, deeply uninformed) family last night concerning the wave of news yesterday. What made me feel bad is essentially just the observation that, despite something of historic proportions occurring, events which ones would have led to an immediate response from the legislative branch, they seemed entirely ambivalent. It's just altogether very disheartening.
column30: The situation is definitely as negative as it seems, and I definitely don't see a silver lining insofar as what it indicates about the temperature and engagement of the broader body politic. I suppose the useful piece of information to be gained is simply that this is where we are at, and whether I like it or not, I need to either find a more effective way to get through to them (unlikely), or accept that there is simply no getting through to them at all and moving on. I don't know if the situation is permanent, and I don't know it will improve. All I can really do is focus on having a more positive response to it.

column17: My husband forgot to ask about when he can take his vacation time yesterday. I wanted to really narrow down the dates so we can purchase airline tickets.
column30: He'll eventually ask. I know he's busy at work, so it's probably one of the last things on his mind. It's not bad because we'll eventually figure it out.

column17: I am on a diet. I have done really well this week until today. Today I ate more than I should have because I didn't measure well and I didn't want to throw away food.
column30: It's not that bad, because I learned that I have to really watch what I'm doing or my tummy feels weird now. I can definitely fix this.

column17: I felt bad because I was moving to a new apartment and it was a stressful time. I don't like having to pack everything up and then quickly unpack everything again. I feel still annoyed about it all even though I knew it was coming.
column30: I guess that I am probably just one more move away from being more established at one place. So all in all I am closer to that point where I won't have to keep moving.

column17: I felt so bad all day,I lost the necklace my daughter gave to me. She is making jewelry now,and had made a beautiful necklace, her first piece,and she gave it to me yesterday. I put it on this morning while walking the dog,and I lost it. I must not have had the clasp closed I have slight trouble with my hands.I was very sad!
column30: It will get better. I told my daughter,and she assures me she will make me another one just like it. I am happier about things now

column17: My oldest son started his first day of school today. I felt an extreme amount of anxiety leaving my son for the first time for such a long period of time in an unknown environment. My son seemed confused but not unhappy with me leaving him. I don't want things to change in my life like my kids growing up and going to school.
column30: This situation isn't negative at all, it's actually really good for my son to be going to school. He's going to learn so much and have a lot of fun doing so. I'll be able to get back to real work as soon as both of my kids are in school. I will gain a lot of satisfaction from my ability to work and my kids both being cared for in a learning environment. This situation is permanent, my kids will be in school for the rest of our time together but it will be time well spent.

column17: I had to wait for an issue with my bank to resolve itself. I could not impact this and unfortunately I had to wait longer than I wanted for it to get resolved.
column30: While I could not affect the situation I did do my best to make sure that the damage was limited or erased so it could not harm me financially.

column17: I have had problems with my neighbors for about nine years now. I finally got tired of being harassed by them and went to a nearby town and looked for a lawyer. I went to three and they didn't do what I needed. They did only car wrecks or other things. I found one and she seemed perfect and told me what I needed to do and to call her and let her know how it went.  One of the neighbors bothering me is a cop. After I left her office I saw a car of two cops and when I called her a few days later, she didn't answer her phone, her door or two emails I sent her.  So it looks like the cops are with their buddy cop and went to pump her for information about what I was at her place for and turned her against me. Now I don't have a lawyer and every time I find one , they are going to try to find out about it and scare them into not helping me. I am very scared and worried about what is happening to me and what is going to happen to me because of these people.
column30: When I talked to the county attorney, he said to move and I told him I already have my house listed. That made me feel like moving isn't a big deal. I can handle it and it will be so much better when I do move. I will be so happy to be away from these people and this area. It will be like a vacation and a dream to be around people who are normal and nice. I can't wait to do it.

column17: An event of situation that took place in the past two days that bothered me was when i was talking to my neighbor and he made a remark that bothered me. This remark was about something that i was wearing and bothered me. During this time I felt self conscious, embarrassed, angry, and wanting to say something to make him look bad. My thoughts at this time were that I was going to get him back, did not like what he said, and thinking about how bad my clothes were that I was wearing.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because it was just a remark that my neighbor made that does not really mean anything. The sliver lining to this situation is that the neighbor is open minded and down to earth which means they are easy to talk to and can have fun. I could learn or gain something useful from this situation by allowing myself to not take things so serious and learn to not be so offended by small comments that are not true. This situation is not permanent because my neighbor is the only one who knows about it and does not represent anything that is set in stone or a large group of people know about. This situation will approve over time because we will both forget about it and not everyone knows about what happen.

column17: I saw in the news that they found the body of Mollie Tibbetts.
column30: Yes, she is dead, that's pretty negative. They guy who killed her confessed and is in custody, so I guess that could be considered a silver lining because he's off the street. I didn't learn anything from this. Death is permanent, yes.

column17: This morning my father lost his iPhone and asked/forced me to help him look for it. It was an extremely stressful experience as his phone is very important to him for his business and he was freaking out and screaming and making me not want to help him at all really, but I still knew how much he wanted the phone so I helped him look for it anyway. Currently, I am very tired due to how much searching we did, and emotionally drained due to the whole experience really.
column30: This is a bit of a tough for me to try and reframe honestly. I guess the positive to the situation is that perhaps my father will learn to be more mindful of what he does, and/or perhaps he will finally learn to realize how out of control his anger is, and he will learn to reel it in. I suppose I could also reframe the situation by considering the fact that it could be a good opportunity for my father to realize he doesn't need such an expensive phone, especially if he's going to lose it. It's hard to say I gained something useful from this situation really, but I don't think the situation is that negative, for me at least.

column17: Yesterday I went to the convenience store store to pick up something to eat on the way home; I didn't feel like cooking. The cashier asked about my t-shirt which has a gaming-related joke on it. It probably sounds odd, but I don't actually like people asking about it (which makes one wonder why I wear it) mostly because I don't want to have to take the time to explain it to strangers. She asked about it and, I was kind of in a hurry. It was late (around 2 am) and I just wanted to get back home so I acted dismissive about it and probably seemed rude. I think that I'm not very good with people and I probably make the people I casually interact with hate me just because of my visible disinterest. Social situations make me feel awkward and like I'm under pressure and I end up coming off rude. I hate that about myself. I feel embarrassed of my dismissive attitude and disappointed in myself that I wasn't more outgoing and friendly. I wish I could be a better person.
column30: Honestly it isn't something that matters and I know that. The cashier probably doesn't even remember me, I'm just one of a thousand faces she sees every day. There are no real silver linings to the situation, just that I could learn to control my responses better. That I could not let little things bother me. I suppose the best thing I can think of about the situation is how little it matters. I wasn't outright rude and I didn't curse or yell... I just looked a bit annoyed and wasn't what one would consider ideally social. I don't guess its anything to be that upset about.

column17: One of my coworkers is out this week and I am backing his accounts up. He is a super nice guy, but left no notes. His clients are making requests that are very different then what I am used it. I am having trouble handling these correctly with nothing to go off of. I ended up messing something up that affected his client. She was quite upset. I was able to call her and apologize, but this was frustrating. This makes me look bad. I am annoyed and frustrated.
column30: This situation is unfortunate, but not the end of the world. My coworker comes back into the office Monday so I will be in better shape then. If I learned anything it is to work with my team and ensure we are prepared to back someone up when they are gone for a significant time. I am learning about new processes, which is great for development. I just wish this was handled a little better. The situation should be resolved by early next week.

column17: I had a list of chores to get done by Tue. and I wasn't  able to remotely achieve it.  I did make sure to prioritize with the time I had and do what was important off the list but the vast majority remained undone.  When that happens I feel disappointed in myself, kind of like I'm worthless.  Like I failed.
column30: Every day I have too many tasks and always have to prioritize.  These days I did that.  Number one is earn what I need and I did do this every day.  Then....keep the house in order and attend to kids' school, and I did that too.  Then do my college , which I did too.  But that was all really.  I hardly got any of the extra tasks done.  But I can respect that still, I got a lot done.  Also , I had a bad burn on my hand from a week ago so my hand usage was impaired to a degree.  I can respect that I dd try hard, and did the important things.  I guess that if those undone things get important I will get to them.  Also, if I didn't go on Facebook and check email so much, I would have gotten them done.  But those relax me and I feel I need them to break up working all day like 14 hours a day 6 days a week like I try to do.

column17: I made a mistake at work, it was dumb. I cut some window trim boards to the wrong size. I feel like I was being careless, the mistake itself isn't what is bothering me. I feel like I was not focused, which makes me feel bad because I think of myself as a focused and reliable person, I don't make mistakes. It makes me a little worried that I am losing that aspect of myself. I keep thinking that maybe i'm not as smart as I think I am.
column30: The boards themselves were easily cut again and replaced, but my mental confidence is shaken by such a small thing, but I will get over it and forget soon enough. No one else even knows about my mistake. I just need to use this event as something to remember, to help me stay focused, because a careless mistake in another area could've been big financial problems. This will soon be forgotten, after a while with no mistakes, my confidence in myself will be full again.

column17:
Two days ago, a friend took to the grocery store and offered to buy me a few things. Bear in mind, even though Joe is a good friend, he tends to look at the negative side of things, and has a judgmental attitude a good deal of the time. But he's been a friend for over 20 years and has helped me out a lot, so I can't just end the friendship because of his judgmental comments. 

So getting back to the point, he took me to the grocery store which sells very nice produce and I was happy to go there with him. Since he called me out of the blue, I kind of was expecting him to go on about his relationship woes, but he didn't really. Nor did he talk about his political opinions ad nauseam, which he can do. So I really shouldn't complain, but I'm going to. As we were putting our stuff onto the checkout area, he made a little snide comment about a product I was buying (or rather, he was buying me) but this little comment irritated me. No one else would have made such a comment. So I let it get to me, and it's still bothering me. It's not so much the one comment, but the comments he keeps making on a continuous basis. I feel judged. I shouldn't feel this way, since he's the one being judgmental, but I do anyways.  I really need to let it go, since I got the food I wanted.
column30: The situation should be as negative as it seems - I'm just making it that way by not letting go of what happened. I shouldn't take it personally, because it's just him being judgmental; it doesn't really have much to do with me. The silver lining to the situation is that I don't have to react this way. I can choose not to. I'm the better person. He has to live with his narrow mindedness, I don't. I can learn from this situation, something I need to learn from this type of situation every time it happens. I need to either say something right then and there, such as some type of comment to stop him in his tracks, or let it go.  I can't not say anything then stress out about it for days. No, this situation is not permanent. He's going to forget all about it. So I'm the only one being bothered by it. So I have to realize that.

column17: My brother asked me to go to my nephew's football jamboree saturday morning.  I moved my schedule around so I could go.  I had a birthday party for my kids on Sunday and he couldn't go because they had a different party, even though he knew about mine first.  I am pretty mad and disappointed that I rearrange my schedule for him, but he can't do the same for me.
column30: I believe the situation is as negative as it seems.  This isn't the first time he's done this, so I really should stop doing things for him because he can't make time for my kids.  The silver lining, I suppose, would be that my kids had a blast without him and my nephews there.  My son's friend from school came and they had a wonderful time.

column17: A mistake in my work was pointed out to me. I made an error in judgment pertaining to reporting and data entry. I have made similar errors in the past. I rehash how I went about it in an unfocused way and should know better. IT's a simple and inconsequential thing, and indicative of how meaningless I feel my work is that such a "dumb" thing would be highlighted. I now reflect about how stuck I feel in my current situation, but I lack the skill set necessary to advance.
column30: It's not the importance of this specific event, and the feedback was meant to simply call attention to how I need to be doing things. It was just representative of showing me how I need to process my work. It was a teaching situation. Generally, very little in terms of errors are pointed out to me, particularly compared to many of my coworkers.

column17: I talk to my Grandma every night on my walk home from work. The other day she told me that she has been diagnosed with both wet and dry forms of macular degeneration and she is starting an experimental treatment that she described as a surgery where they inject something into her eye and then she has to keep it covered and put drops in it for a day. Overnight she lost a large percentage of her vision and it is very hard for her to get around now. I feel so bad for her even though she seems to be taking it well. I am mostly sad that I cannot be there for her since she is a few states away. I hope I can go see her before she loses all of her vision.
column30: I should not worry about it as much as I have since she is coping with it quite well. I have done some research on visual aids she can purchase to help her still enjoy things like reading and puzzling, so I have learned a bit about that and about macular degeneration in general. It seems to be something that naturally happens to many of us as we get older. I'm not sure if this is permanent or if it can improve, but I hope that the experimental treatment does help for her.

column17: I've had a couple of arguments with my wife mainly because we have some financial issues and I should have put in some extra hours and made more money.  She is right and I feel bad about it. But I can't change what happened so I feel like she should give me a break once in a while.  She is always so worried about money and it's like she completely forgot how to have fun and take it easy.
column30: The silver lining is that at least we communicate with each other and this situation is only temporary,  I'm sure it will pass

column17: My mother came from my home country today after 2 years of waiting. We talked about different things and the most important one was the topic of moving out, I have to get a place for both of us for a while at least. She doesn't speak English and I'm a little stressed because of I'm not financially ready to move out for at least 2 months. The issue is I may not have much time due to other personal reasons.
column30: My mother finally came after 2 years of struggle and waiting, although things are a little rough right now I have hopes that we can move out soon. Things will not be permanent and the situation is not as bad as I make it seem, I just tend to worry a lot.

column17: An event that took place in the past two days that bothers me is when someone threatened me over something they did not need to and they would not come to their senses and realize they do not have to speak to me like I am a child. I do not like not being shown respect. My current feelings and thoughts toward the event is that I accept that the way that person acts toward me is a core part of their personality and it is not personal. However I am still annoyed by this person for not showing me respect and speaking to me in a certain way.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because this person is not trying to be mean on purpose. The silver lining to this situation is that it taught me how to better respond to people who I feel are being mean. I think I learned how to keep a calmer head in response to people being rude to me and learning how to not take everything so personal. This situation is not permanent and it can be improved by simply keeping my distance from certain people or being willing to accept that I should let some things go.

column17: I saw someone I didn't want to talk to walking towards me. I pretended I didn't see them and I crossed the street to avoid them. I do feel badly about this.
column30: I saw someone I know walking towards me. I was busy so I crossed the street to avoid them.

column17: The store that I pre ordered a game at didn't have it in stock for me when I went there to pick it up.  One of their new employees dropped the ball and I was out of luck.  They weren't very empathetic towards my issues and there wasn't anything they could do about it.  Now I'm bored because I don't have anything to do.
column30: I'm not sure what I could do different about the situation.  Maybe I could workout or use my free time without the game to do something productive.

column17: I was sick the past two days. I felt like a wreck and weak because I was sick. Even though it was just a cold and fever it did making me felt like a failure. Now, I am getting a little better with a bit of coughing.
column30: Getting sick at this age is quite negative for me. My fault was I did not get to the doctor when I first notice the symptoms. I kept delaying my doctor appointments and it had gone worse two days ago. The situation can be improved if I did not delay it. Lesson learned next time when I catch a cold go to the doctor immediately.

column17: My nearly-adult child is living out of state and wanted me to send his birth certificate for ID to get his license there.  Since the MVD site clearly says that the parent listed on the certificate must be a resident of that state, for ID purposes of a minor, and I'm NOT a resident of that state and also because I do NOT agree to assume financial responsibility for his driving while he's of state and that he needs to just wait the few short weeks until he's 18 and can handle it all on his own....he informed me that his dad singed his application, in absolute clear violation of the rules of "who can sign".  His dad has zero custody of him and CAN'T sign, especially  without me, and my son said the MVD accepted that signature......so it's a ball of legal BS potentially, and I know my son is upset that I won't send the birth certificate, I'm upset that my ex would sign what it clearly says on the application he can't sign.  I'm not sure how it impacts me legally or if it does at all.  I'm upset that my son's upset. .....
column30: I think it's probably not negative in the big picture and not permanent.  I always do what I think and know to be right whether or not it pleases my child so it's just another in a long line of unpopular decisions I've made.  I'm not trying to be his friend, but it does upset me when I have to say "no" to something he wants a lot.  He's working a lot and trying hard and I know he wants his license.  I can't think of anything that I can personally take from this or learn.

column17: My mom talked to me about some family medical history. I went to the ER in June for some fertility issues. We talked about our family's fertility problems and how they may relate to me. I'm a bit down, but glad I know this since I have a doctor's appointment coming up.
column30: The only good thing is in less than a month I'll get some answers. But it stinks until then. It will be good to finally know about what's wrong with my ovaries.

column17: My son was struggling at football practice.  He is scared of contact and hitting and a lot slower than the other kids.
column30: Maybe he will come around and start playing better.  he loves the game and just competing even if he is lacking talent seems to make him okay.  The coach put him at wide receiver so he doesn't have to do much but he thinks its cool.

column17: This morning my brother came downstairs to tell me he was going back to jail for a parole violation. I was pretty distant towards him because I'd been hoping that this would happen and it's not entirely clear if it's actually true as he is a habitual liar. I feel bad for being so distant and I think it hurts his feelings, but I really can't help myself.
column30: The situation isn't as negative as it seems. I feel bad, but he's a real jerk and at the end of the day I don't really care what he thinks. He preys upon people who are nice to him. He's hopefully gone back to jail which is a silver lining as he will stop taking advantage of my parents. Maybe next time he gets out he will be better. I just feel bad for having been hoping he winds up going back to jail.

column17: My girlfriend and I were fighting last night about how much I am on mturk. I have been able to make a good amount of money doing MTURK daily and trying to balance it with hanging out with family and friends. She feels like I am neglecting her, but I treat her very well. This is worrying me as I do not want to scale my working on mturk. The money has been really helpful and I would be annoyed if I had to stop. It is a frustrating situation.
column30: The situation could be worse. I need to do a better job balancing everything in life. I will try to adjust the times that I do turk in order to spend more time with my girlfriend. I know I can do a better job. I think this will be something I will have to balance for a while since I am getting better at turking each day. This will be challenging, but can be done.

column17: I was contacting a requester on MTurk to try and overturn what I considered to be an unfair rejection. The requester accused me of not being authentic, and I assume was implying that I was trying to scam them out of money. Currently I do not feel stressed because the situation is mostly resolved, but it's still a bit frustrating to have my values questioned, as I consider myself to be a very honest and ethical individual.
column30: I think I can reframe the situation by thinking about how it feels like from their point of view. They probably saw my completion time, which seemed exceptionally fast, and came to the (what I consider false) conclusion that I must have been a scammer. This situation presents an opportunity for me to consider situations from another point of view, and allows me the opportunity to practice staying composed in a negative situation, and calmly explaining my side, while still being respectful. In that regard, there is a lot to learn from such a situation.

column17: I got lazy one or two days and did not work as much as I could because I had most of my bills sorted out for the week.
column30: I can try to use these past two days to motivate myself to do better and not fall into a hole of laziness. I learned that I should be doing better or working harder. The situation is temporary and can improve due to my efforts.

column17: I feel like a significant amount of these kinds of events and situations have happened to me somewhat recently. I lost out on a number of work opportunities through no fault of my own that really should have not been an issue for me. This caused me to become demotivated and to avoid seeking out other opportunities, which has caused me to lose some progress on my recent task progression. For me, this ends up turning into a cycle where I just fall further and further behind and then exhaust myself trying to catch up, overworking myself and then becoming demotivated, causing the cycle to perpetuate.
column30: Perhaps it would be best to move on from these situations as many of them are over and done with, and maybe, I can take what I have learned to inform my future performance. I would not be surprised if I just continue to make these same mistakes again, but there is always a chance that I can get something out of what happened. It doesn't matter as much as other issues I might face, at least.

column17: Today at work,we all learned that our hours will be cut,and they are putting in place a hiring freeze,and a raise freeze. Thats going to be tough,because now,the same amount of work still has to be done. We will be forced to do more work,with no extra pay,and in less time,but in the end,because of the hours cut,we will still be bringing home less than we were before,while doing more than before. Everybody at work is pissed!
column30: This situation is not permanent,it has happened before in the past. The good thing is,it shouldnt last very long. A month tops. Then things will get back to normal,I hope!

column17: This afternoon I took my two kids outside to play. I knew that we've had a lot of mosquitoes in our yard but wasn't prepared for them today. The mosquitoes pretty much went after every inch of my kids' exposed skin. Even getting my kids in the house as soon as I noticed the problem wasn't enough to save them from all of the bites. My youngest son swells from the bites and is bad about scratching. I feel like I failed my kids by letting this happen to them.
column30: The situation could have gone better but at least my kids got to go outside to play even briefly. I did have an ointment on hand to treat the bites and they will soon heal. I'll know for the next time that I take the kids out of the house to prepare them with long sleeves and bug repellent. I gave the kids a quick shower after they came in to take away some of the itchiness of their bites and hopefully in a few hours they won't be bothered by them any more.

column17: My car broke down on the highway which was difficult to deal with because I was making a long drive at the time. I am still upset about it.
column30: I guess that no one was hurt and it is a fixable situation in terms of the car so it can get better in a sense. I really hope never to have to deal with it again.

column17: My husband and I got into an argument last night. I said some things I really shouldn't have, just to hurt his feelings. It makes me feel like a jerk. I still feel like a jerk for saying the things I did.
column30: I can learn to keep my mouth shut. I can learn to think before I speak and to not say things in the heat of the moment. That will help me in my relationships with everyone in my family.

column17: My truck has a flat tire and I am going to need to get it replaced. I don't have much money, so any unplanned for expenses like this are bad news for me. It makes me feel bad that I don't have enough money, or didn't save enough when I could. The tire has to be fixed because I need to be able to drive. It makes me feel like I am failing financially because I can't keep up with the costs of life. It makes me compare myself to how others are doing with money and brings me down.
column30: I know I have had events like this in the past, and it always worked out eventually. I am not going to go bankrupt or anything, I just have to adjust my life a bit. I can use this as a wakeup call to get my money issues in order and start being more responsible. Feeling bad about myself isn't going to help anything, and people probably aren't looking down on me like I imagine. Almost everybody has trouble paying bills sometimes, I am just normal. The tire was getting bald anyway, it's a smaller issue than I was making it out to be.

column17: I paid my bills for the month off yesterday and watched as all the money I'd been building up for month vanished with the press of a button. It really underscored how much I'd been spending this month and how little I have to show for it. It's a reminder to me that I'm not doing as well as I should be. I don't make a lot of money, not as much as my family and friends. It reminds me that I'm a failure. I feel as though I'm a failure as a person, spinning my wheels and not really going anywhere. I feel as though I've just wasted the past decade of my life on dead-end jobs and goofing off while I could have been making more of myself. It's a silly think to feel, I guess, over something so little. Watching the money in my bank account slip back to what it was at the first of the month, but it still leaves me feeling depressed.
column30: I suppose it could be worse. I don't have any real debt hanging over my head and I have a place to live. I'm not in constant fear for my well-being at my home like some people are. I don't make a lot of money but I'm also doing well enough; I have food to eat every day and a home and electricity and internet. The silver lining is, even though I spent most of of what I earned this month I don't have any debt hovering over me at the moment. I could use this as an opportunity to evaluate what I spend and maybe cut things out of my life that I don't really need or use as much. I think the situation can improve, but it would require me to change as a person and to grow into someone more responsible and ambitious.

column17: Nothing like this happened to me in the last two days.
column30: No, because nothing bad happened to me in the last two days.

column17: I was supposed to leave work early to go to my parents house for the weekend and my boss kept me late and I missed the last train. It is incredibly annoying and i'm so frustrated.
column30: Yes it is as negative adn there is no sivler lining. It's not permanent but it's definitely really frustrating.

column17: An even that happened in the past two days that still bothers me is when I seen my moms Ex boyfriend at the store. During this time I was going to the store to go shopping when I was standing there and my moms ex boyfriend who cheated on her walked past me. During this time I felt very angry and that I wanted to hit or hurt him. My current feelings are that I am mad and wish to tell him how much he hurt my mom and that I would like him to understand what he did.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because I was just seeing someone from the past that does not have a current effect of meaning on my life unless I let them. I can not see any silver linings to the situation other than that I did not have to interact or do something that I would regret in the future. I could learn or gain something from this in that  I can control my emotions and I let the person know that I am not going to allow them to make me feel bad or control my emotions. This situation is not permanent because I am the only one that knows about it, and nothing really happen other than walking pass each other.

column17: My boyfriend is great most of the time, but he has a habit of liking to get under my skin and will not apologize when I get upset. Last night he farted on me on the couch, and then wrestled me until I just got so mad that I went to bed. Then in bed he denied that he ever farted on me and claimed that I'm always farting on him. It shouldn't bother me, but it does. It upsets me when he doesn't remember things that I remember so vividly and then acts like I'm making it all up. I don't know if I really need an apology, but it would be nice if he could at least validate my acknowledge my feelings and not try to get under my skin like that. I don't know why he would want to cause conflict like that.
column30: It's not very negative, it's just frustrating. I try to talk to him and it doesn't help when he doesn't even acknowledge the problem. I think what I could learn from this is that I need to deal with the situation as it is happening instead of running away because I'm mad/upset. It is hard for me to do that because I clam up when I'm upset. I think if I started working on this though it would improve this situation and future situations like it. This isn't a big deal, but it is something that needs to be addressed. It is definitely a temporary problem.

column17: I went out shopping with my mother last night, which we commonly do every week. We often spar, but I was particularly irritable and defensive when I felt she was attacking my judgments. On recurring issues. I attacked back, on a personal and hurtful level at her, hell-bent on demeaning her as a person, a woman, a parent, wife, and any other context I could think of. It did not end well, although I know it will blow over quickly. I try constantly to make living amends to both her and my father for what I put them through, and because of the immeasurable amount of love and gratitude that I have for them. I was extraordinarily disrespectful, and I thought I had matured and evolved past the place that I went to in the past years of my recovery. I hate it when I regress so profoundly mentally and emotionally and toward a person I owe my life to, and that has nothing to do with merely giving birth to me.
column30: I am able to step back and take my own inventory. I have apologized and am the recipient of her forgiveness. I am lucky enough to have unconditional love from this person. I have the good fortune to be close to my parents, and the ability to now make up for lost years, and in a meaningful way. In my three years of sobriety, I now have a relationship with my mother, and disagreements are a natural and perhaps healthy thing. The context of our fleeting falling out are so minimal compared to past situations. I can recognize the value of our relationship. It is growth.

column17: I left my drunk friend at the pub. I didn't want to give him a ride home because I didn't want him to throw up in my car. He's done it before. But now I feel guilty about it because I'm sure he overpaid for a taxi. I don't  think he'll remember much of anything tomorrow.
column30: Come to think about it it's his fault that he almost always has too much to drink when we go out together.  And I've always been a good friend to him it's just that these days I simply can't afford to have my car cleaned and I can't show up at home with the car smelling like puke. My wife and I share the car and she would definitely throw a fit if she found out I've been out drinking with my buddy , even though I didn't have to pay for anything.

column17: I've been thinking about moving out since the situation calls for it at this point, the problem I had is still there and its the financial one. I just don't have the money to move out at this point and I don't know how much time I have left to stay at my current place. This has been getting me a bit stressed since I can't really do much more for now.
column30: In regards to my moving situation, things don't look too great but it's not as bad if I make it out to be if I think about it. I'm getting support from my mother whos also going to be moving in with me and I still think I have some time left, not sure how much tho. The situation is obviously not permanent, I hope that within 1-2 months I will be better off and resolve this situation. I always tend to over worry about things so I end up being stressed, I am hopeful things can change for the better.

column17: I went out to eat and the server got my order wrong.  I was already having a bad day and it just compounded the issues I was having.  I was looking forward to having my favorite meal and the server told me that they no longer had what I wanted to eat for dinner.
column30: Well since I am on a diet, having a less calorie dense meal would be beneficial to me, so maybe it was a blessing in disguise.

column17: A event that took place recently is that I was at a convenience store and parked on the side of it. A suspicious looking man came up to the side of my window and asked for a light. It was night time so I was a bit suspicious and told him I dropped my lighter. He asked if he could use the cigarette. I let him use the cigarette but I was nervous and watching him closely to make sure he did not pull out a weapon. I was upset for letting myself be in this situation because if he had wanted to do me harm I had put myself in a bad situation where there were no witnesses. My current thoughts and feelings is that I am annoyed but relieved that nothing happened.
column30: This situation is not as bad as it seems because nothing happened and it is in the past now. The silver lining to this situation is that I will no longer park in areas that have no witnesses. I will no longer park in areas where I am by myself. I learned something useful in the sense that I learned to be smarter when moving throughout the world to make sure I can stay safe. This situation is not permanent  and it can improve by not making the same mistake again.

column17: I put off doing a task I knew I would not enjoy. This makes me feel bad because I'm just delaying the inevitable.
column30: I put off doing a difficult task. But I know I'll be able to tackle it tomorrow.

column17: A couple of days ago I met up with my ex as we pretty much are on good speaking terms. We usually get along pretty good, but I know that he wants to have sex with me; something that I absolutely do not want to do. Everything was going fine until out of nowhere he made a lewd comment to me and I was pretty offended. After telling him that he was being inappropriate, he seemed hurt, but that was his problem and I told him so. But I haven't been able to get this out of my head. I want to let it go, as that just shows his maturity level and I don't want to stoop to his level.
column30: Although it seems pretty negative to me, it probably isn't as bad as it seems. I just have to put it into perspective. He was just being his immature self and I was being the mature adult, so I could have felt good about myself for being vocal about my feelings. There is a silver lining that I can and will be the bigger person. I don't have to be insulted at his immaturity.  I can gain something useful by continuing to be vocal and get pretty good at coming up with comebacks and let him remain the immature one. With him being as immature as he is I don't know if the situation can be improved. But my reaction to it can. I have to stop letting him get under my skin.

column17: I went out with my ex-girlfriend and I still have not told my wife about it. I feel bad to hide from her. I am still feeling bad and wrong to go out with my ex-girlfriend. We even had a fancy dinner and probably would meet again because I work near her place. I feel like I am cheating on my wife.
column30: It is negative when you keep something from your spouse. I think I would try to avoid her next time. Only meet when necessary. I will try to talk to my wife after a day or two.

column17: Someone did something very recently that made some work for me. It's not the most difficult thing I've had to deal with, but I just did not expect it. I am already feeling stressed because of my many obligations, and I am wondering how I will find time to work on this task. If I don't do it or ask to have more time on it, I am concerned others might make me feel guilty or be mad at me. I want to work on it, but I just have other priorities I also have to deal with.
column30: I guess it's not so bad because I made good progress towards my goals today. This makes it more likely that I will be less busy later. I don't mind doing the kind of work that it involves either - it is different than what I normally do. There are probably not many things about the task that will be surprising or odd - it will probably be pretty straightforward and will give me a chance to do something different.

column17: I got onto my oldest son last night for staying up too late.  He got frustrated which made me more frustrated.  I hate going to bed after a spat.
column30: He needs to learn that I mean business.  What I say goes and he has to listen otherwise I as the parent have the right to get upset.

column17: The semester just started and over the weekend I took my first two quizzes in my new course.  In several places on the first one I noticed more than one equally true options on the multiple choice quizzes.  I even looked up the answers just to make sure and there wasn't a "more correct" option.  They were both equally correct.  As I went through the 2nd quiz, the same.  So this tells me that the whole semester, probably, will have this every week.  I don't think this should happen.  I did email my professor about them but I really don't want to do this each week .  I think he will resent it and find me pesky, instead of the quiz format being the problem.
column30: The whole course is only 7 1/2 weeks (condensed) so the worse it will be is 7 1/2 weeks of bs quizzes.  Also, this instructor gives a lot of opportunities to pick up extra points so I can probably make up any that are lost on the quizzes where I PICK a CORRECT answer (verifiable in many sources to be correct) but have it marked wrong because I didn't choose the OTHER correct option.  SMH.  This, in the scheme of things, isn't that important but I had to find something for this HIT and it was the only thing I could think of.  To see it differently I guess a positive is that the instructor will know that I know my stuff if I can notice and successfully argue my case on these questions.

column17: An event that bothered me in the past two days is when my cat chewed through my cox cord and had my internet shut off. That annoyed me because this cat always causes problems for you. I feel bad because I should have known to put dishwasher soap on the cord so that this could not happen. My current thoughts and feelings is that I have since fixed the problem, but I am annoyed that I had to go through that. I am annoyed that cats can cause so much trouble.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because I fixed the problem as I had no choice. The silver lining to this situation is that I now know to make sure that I coat my wires with dish washer soap so that the cat does not want to taste the wire. I learned to not trust cats. The situation is not permanent and it can be improved by me getting rid of the cat or putting dishwashing soap on my wires.

column17: My friend Nick at the bar seems kind of standoffish lately. I don't think that I did anything to piss him off, but he's been weird the last week or two. It's possible I did something, but again I don't think so. It keeps coming to mind and I don't have a clear answer.
column30: I'm not even sure the situation is negative. He may just be grumpy with something in his personal life, but if thats the case I wish he'd complain about it or something. It's really not a big deal. I could make sure when I'm in a bad mood to not make my friends feel like maybe they did something wrong. The situation is likely temporary. Even if I did upset him he'll get over it.

column17: My husband's aunt was talking down to me again on Saturday evening. It really upsets me. She has no disregard for others. She points out things that she thinks is a problem, but doesn't realize she does stuff way worse. It was about money this week, and why my husband chose to fix somethings in his car himself, rather than to pay someone to do it.
column30: We're going to move out eventually. so this isn't a permanent situation.

They continue to pass it off to the next person and have not completed it yet. Finally, the original person has it again and they still passed it off. Adding a supervisor did not help either. I am annoyed and frustrated by how much time was wasted because no one will take ownership of the issue. It is a common problem.
column30: This could be worse, because it is not actively hurting our client. Essentially they have been completed, but need to be closed. That makes me feel better, but still want to have everything closed and completed. I have learned a few new contacts to reach out to if I am not getting an answer. I expect this to be resolved soon, but sadly I expect these issues to continually occur.

column17: My son is sick after being in school for two days. He's feeling fairly miserable as he has a runny nose and his eyes keep tearing up from sinus pressure. I know that it's only a matter of time before he gets his brother sick even though I'm trying to limit their contact. I feel so badly for my child feeling this way.
column30: Being sick is a natural part of life. Being sick will help my son to improve his natural immunity. Maybe I should be thankful that my son is sick now before flu season arrives. My son should be feeling better in just a few days, for now I can just take care of him the best that I can.

column17: Yesterday I was cleaning out the garage looking for the furniture clamps that we have out there when I stumbled upon a box of my old toys from when I was a kid. I was already feeling in a nostalgic mood, so I dug them out just to have a look. There were a bunch of my old things there, an old model steam locomotive that my father and I used to play with. It reminded me of when we used to build model trains when I was younger and it really made me feel down. I also found, in the bottom of the box, some old die-cast sesame street cars from when I was a kid. A few of them were broken, their wheels had gotten mashed from their time in the box and some of the paint had gotten scratched. It really made me sad, it made me miss the past and my youth. Made me miss my parents and made me regret that I didn't take care of my things better. I feel like I never give things the care and attention they deserve; that I never do enough. I don't appreciate things while I still have them.
column30: I don't guess the situation is as bad as it might seem. I don't even really play with the toys any more and aside from occasions like this I never really bother to look at them. The past is gone and I accept that. The silver lining, I suppose, is that I still have those old toys. A lot of peoples parents threw them out when they got old. I don't suppose I really learned anything per say. I should appreciate the things that I have more, and I think it's good to have reminders of the past even if it makes us sad. It's good to remember the people and places we used to know, and to keep their memory alive in your heart. It's a good thing, even if it makes you a little sad. I should take care to preserve the memories that I have today and to care for the people around me more.

column17: I spent a good part of the day napping and not being motivated enough to work. I regret this because I have to work harder today now.
column30: Although I did not work as hard as I could I would be more motivated to really get work done this week to make up for it.

More than anything, I think the remarks he was making speak far more to issues with himself than legitimate issues with me, and I should probably have some compassion for him on that front. The situation is not permanent, and while it can certainly improve, I'm not entirely certain that my head is willing to go there at the moment.

column17: The boy that I am dating broke up with me. I feel awful.
column30: it is because i really liked him. However, i guess it is good to find out this early rather than later.

The situation is certainly not as negative as it first seemed, and the situation is definitely improvable as I can certainly change my way of thinking and consider that this event gives me an opportunity to realize that I may have to be more patient in my approach.

Now I am waiting for the plumber to come by to see if he find a permanent solution. It still bothers me because I have never done anything to the pipes or any customization and out of all the days it breaks on me. I just feel mostly flustered and really annoyed.

column17: An event that took place in the past two days that still bothers me is when I was playing a video game with some friends and lost. During this time we were playing a team game online with 2 of my friends when we lost and the people on the other team starting saying negative things and sending us messages. During this time this made me feel bad and stressful because I lost which I do not like and got down on myself. The other reason is that they were really disrespectful and not humble in victory. My current feelings and thoughts are that I want to get back on the game and find them to win and then send them messages so they can feel the way that I did.
column30: The situation is not as negative as it seems because nothing really happened to me or my friends other than coming across some negative people online. There are silver linings in that it does not really matter because it was something that happen online and I do not even know or interact with these people. I could learn or gain that I need to remain calm and realize that it does not really mean anything when you play online and interact with other people online. This situation is not permanent because it is just a one time event that happen online. My friends and I will not think or talk about it in the future.

column17: I've been checking up on the internet regarding the issues I had with my UTI and somehow stumbled upon testicular cancer, I started searching up on this and became extremely worried after I did an amateurish self-check on myself and found a lump. This caused me a great deal of stress and I was actually going nuts. I realized today that I'm most likely wrong and that my worries are unfounded, this still bothers me because you never know(what if). After hours of searching I found out that I was wrong but man I think I need to see a phycologist for some help, I get worried and it just makes everything worse.
column30: The situation was obviously not as bad as I put it, excessive worrying is never good especially when you know nothing about what really wrong with you. Assuming It was the worst case and I had cancer there its still not as bad because of the high success treatments and cures for it. I hope I can move past all this ordeal soon enough and start being more healthy both physically and mentally. I am learning a lot from the situation because I realized that my worries are not doing anything to improve my situation, it's just making it worse.

column17: I contacted a requester a few days ago about a bonus payment for a project I did and am still waiting to get paid. I really need the money and constantly having to wait to get paid when I took the time to do their tasks - time that I could have spent more productively. I feel a bit helpless because there's really nothing I can do to make them pay me. It's totally in their hands. And it's taking up even more of my time contacting them to see what's going on. It's a bit frustrating.
column30: Right now, the situation feels quite negative. Maybe in a few days, it won't seem so bad. I'll have to wait and see. I don't really see a silver lining either. I did the work, another person has it completely in their hands to either pay me or not, and I'm the one who has to stress about it and contact them to try to resolve it. If there is a silver lining, I'm not seeing it yet. I can however, get something useful from this. I have to realize that doing task work has its pros and cons. I should start to expect this is going to happen and be prepared and not count on payment from any one party. I hope this situation gets resolved soon. But there will be more similar situations. It comes with the rioter of working from home. I have to get used to it.

I can look back on this in the future, and realize this little speedbump didn't derail my whole plan, and learn from that and not stress about something like this again. column17: My close friend and sponsor died in Feb. She was elderly and it was not unexpected, but I was out of state and not present for her funeral and last days. Yesterday, two other of her close friends, and surviving husband and I took her ashes to a small memorial church she loved in NC. I am not one for emotionally symbolic events, nor did I wish to be a part of this "vigil." For me, she's simply gone, and I had other matters to attend to, work-related. Still, I went and was resentful and snarky the entire time. I know I have issues relating to a total lack of compassion and detachment, and lack of interest in others, which bothers me when there is such strong evidence as reflected by my behavior. Noticed by others, as well.  I feel I am just a shell of a person, and it is no wonder that I am so lonely. I am a bad friend, and have a stony heart.
column30: It is important that I do the next right thing - to be cliche - and my actions reflected this, if not my emotions. I fulfilled an obligation I felt I had to both my deceased friend and her husband, who wanted me to be present. I suited up and showed up, and ethically my priorities were in order. I put myself in an uncomfortable situation in order to connect with others.

column17: I said I would call my friend later, but I never did. I felt badly about this because I try to keep all my promises.
column30: I said I would call my friend later but I decided to call her tomorrow when I have more time.

(As I predict) It will bring experience working with others.  It's not permanent. column17: The internet went out a couple of times yesterday morning and stayed out the last time. It was a bit aggravating as I was trying to work. It turns out the service was disconnected because the bill wasn't payed. I asked my dad who takes care of the bill what was going on and after talking to him and calling Comcast it turned out he was a month and a half behind. After getting the service turned back on I talked to him about this. He says he can't pay it because the bill comes at the wrong time of the month. I talked to him about budgeting and he got upset. It's important to understand my parents bring in about 6500 a month and total necessary spending it only around 3500. They are just both terrible with money. After talking with my mother it turned out he had been giving large sums of money to my brother all month and was broke as a result(If you keep these together, yeah he didn't go back to jail. I didn't need to feel bad about being cold). I was really upset about this all day on different levels; the interruption in my work, the fact that he didn't ask me to help, the fact that he's giving my brother 1000's of dollars every month that goes to his drug habit, the fact that they are both so terrible with money. I'm still a bit upset about this.
column30: It is negative he is not going to stop giving my brother money. He is not as mentally there as he used to be. He's going to end up getting caught up in one of his schemes and face prosecution. I guess the saving grace/silver lining is I don't have to be here. I just wanted to save up some money before moving out again. It will likely get worse if I'm not around. I'm really having trouble with this one. I don't know how to change my feeling and thoughts about this without trying to change the situation. I mean I guess no one is getting physically hurt. I already took over paying some of the bills, but I feel like I'm just enabling my parents to not worry about money and give it to my brother.

column17: I was at my friends yesterday for our weekly gaming session. It was me and three other friends, we get together often to play games and socialize. One of my friends got into an argument with the host's girlfriend over drama from the past and eventually my friend left out of frustration. I feel bad, I don't like when there's drama or stress with the people I know. I feel disappointed in myself that I chose to cowardly not get involved rather than to try and play the role of peacemaker and to help smooth things over. I regret that I didn't do more to comfort my friend afterward either. Truthfully I just wanted to be somewhere else and for the situation to be over so I wouldn't have to deal with it anymore.
column30: As selfish as it sounds, one positive is that the situation doesn't really involve me. The event they argued about took place in the past and wasn't something I was involved in in any way, so no one is upset at me. I know that's a terrible way to look at things. Honestly, I know it wasn't a relationship-ending affair. It isn't the first time they've argued and things will probably end up being fine, they usually are. It's probably nothing I need to worry about. They're both adults and they can work out their own problems. I should be more supportive though, thats what I've learned. It's not necessarily my place to get involved during a fight, but I should do what I can to make sure that my friends are ok and that I support them emotionally when I can do so.

column17: An event or situation that took place in the past two days that still bothers me is when I was going to adopt a new dog from the local shelter. This situation is not permanent as even though I did not get the dog that I wanted, I will still be able to get one in the future.

column17: Every day I go home for my lunch to let my dogs out for a potty break in the middle of the day. Yesterday the bus driver went right past my stop even though I had rang the bell and there were people waiting at the stop. I yelled that I wanted that stop yet he continued up the street. He finally lets me off and I confront him on why he didn't stop. He claimed that the stop was closed, but I take that stop everyday and told him there were no signs and people were waiting there on top of it. He replied that his notes said it was closed and that he could get in trouble for stopping there when it is closed. Some people were able to run to catch up with the bus but others weren't. I confirmed that the stop was not closed, but by that time the bus was gone. I would have reported it but I didn't get the bus ID number written down so I didn't bother. It just really upset me because I knew I was right, and he was going out of his way to mess up 3 people's day. I guess I should have reported it because it still bothers me and now I'm afraid they are going to skip my stop again.
column30: The situation isn't all that important in the grand scheme of things, it was just frustrating. It wasn't so much negative to me, but I don't know if those people were trying to make it to an appointment or something. The silver lining is that it didn't really affect me, I still got home at the same relative time. I could learn to not get shaken up over trivial things such as this, because everyone makes mistakes and not everyone is nice to interact with. This was very much a temporary situation, and hopefully a one time issue.

column17: I had an idea at work for changing processes to be more effective. I've been using it for awhile now with good results. I had an opportunity to bring this up and share, but did not. This is typical of me to remain silent and in the background, rather than call attention to myself. It is also why I never consciously take leadership roles (though somehow end up with them sometimes) or progress professionally. I reflect on this pattern throughout my life, and I feel a sense of failure and missed opportunities.
column30: My suggestions remain applicable and there is ample opportunity to still bring them up. I have benefitted from my adapted methods personally which is a positive thing and can continue to do so, improving my work performance.

column17: I finally got my blood and urine results back and everything was fine except Vitamin D levels being slightly low but that's nothing concerning. The thing that still has been a bit worried is the slight symptoms and the general discomfort, my doctor said I was perfectly fine but until I get my ultrasound I don't think I'll stop worrying completely. So until I'm completely in the clear I guess I'll still be worrying about the issue.
column30: Today I went and got my results back and thankfully there was nothing wrong with me. While I'm still slightly worried at least I know that everything is fine with my body. My situation is much better than it was 3 weeks ago so it's not as bad as it seems now. I'm learning a lot from the situation because my mental state is getting better, I'm trying to put less emphasis on things and just try to focus less on these things.

column17:
I couple of days ago, I got a couple of tasks I did on another site (not mturk) rejected.The rejections were on tasks that had several criteria to them. They were search tasks where you had to search phrase that you typed in, and couldn't copy and paste, once you found the right site the phrase belonged to, you had to make sure you were on the right site, then you had to stay on the site for a certain amount of time. Then you had to click on a captcha. And you are timed to do all this. So what happened is that the time ran out. And when I went back to do the task again, I skipped all the steps since I had already done them. But since the first time didn't count, they didn't know that I had gone through the task thoroughly, and I'm assuming they go by their timer as the only way of knowing the time I spent. 

I don't know why I am upset about a few cents that I lost, but when you work for pennies, every penny counts. I want to get past worrying about every little cent I miss out on, but it's the principle of the thing. I could contact requester and explain my side of the story, but that would cause more trouble than those hits are worth. So I need to let go and forget about it, but it's something that happens often enough to get me upset when it does happen. So I'm frustrated about having to deal with petty things such as this.
column30: I guess the situation is not as negative as it seems. It's really nothing. $.34, nothing that really matters. I need to let it go. The silver lining in this is that I can chose to let it go and not bother me. I can stop majoring in minor things. It's super irrelevant and I have to see it for what it really is and let it go. I can learn something. Not to do tasks that have so much criteria to them. Then I won't have to worry about not doing them to their standard. This situation can improve once I move on and stop thinking about it. It's so irrelevant.

column17: I haven't had anything happen to make me feel bad.
column30: There was nothing that happened to make me feel bad.

column17: I have been stressed because last night I had a toothache, which is very rare for me. I have one tooth with a dark spot, but it has never bothered me for years. I am worried that it may need medical attention. I am scared of going to the dentist. The pain felt very strange and not like a normal pain. It makes me feel like I might not be taking care of my teeth as well as I thought I was, and not being responsible enough. I don't have enough money if it is something serious with the tooth, which makes me stress out.
column30: Going to the dentist is not going to kill me. I could probably use a tooth checkup anyway, so maybe it is a blessing in disguise. I can learn from this and take better care of my teeth and avoid sugary foods that get stuck and cause cavities. The pain wasn't even severe like I know tooth pain can be, and I have had similar pain before and nothing major came of it. I can learn from this and start taking better care of my health in other ways too.

column17: I was in a rush to get to my apartment. I saw someone trying to get to the elevator, but did not hold the door for them. I feel badly about this.
column30: I was in a rush to get to my apartment. I saw someone coming, but did not hold the elevator door because I knew it would only be a minute before it was on the ground floor again.

column17: An event that is a source of stress for me in the past two days is when I had to wait for a long time in a fast food drive through because the people inside were getting overwhelmed and could not handle it. I had to keep asking for assistance in the speaker. They were taking so long I had to eventually just leave because if I had waited any longer it would not of been worth it when I eventually did get my food. That fast food place is my favorite and I was looking forward to that and was very disappointed I could not get it that night.
column30: This situation is not as negative as it seems because fast food is not good for me anyway. The silver lining to the situation is that it showed me not to go to the fast food place at that time. I learned nothing useful from this situation except to not go to a fast food drive through at around 9 PM. This situation is not permanent and it can be improved by me going to the fast food place at a different time when it is not so busy.
